Name: Bassa (basa), steamed or poached

Name: Pizza, ham & pineapple, thick base, fast food chain-style

Name: Biscuit, sweet, sandwich, cream & jam filling

Name: Grape, black muscatel, raw

Name: Veal, loin chop, separable lean, raw

Name: Sauce, black bean, Asian, commercial

Name: Tofu (soy bean curd), burger pattie, as purchased

Name: Apricot, canned in pear juice, juice only
Pumpkin, jarrahdale, peeled, raw

Name: Mutton, leg roast, untrimmed, raw

Name: Salmon, red, canned in brine

Name: Cheese, cheddar, processed
Description: Australian produced processed cheddar cheese. Major ingredients include cheese and salt. Prepared by grinding, mixing, melting and emulsifying one or more varieties of cheese to form a homogeneous mass. Supplied as slices or blocks.

Name: Yoghurt, low fat (<0.5%), apricot pieces or flavoured
Description: Australian produced low fat yoghurt with apricot pieces and added sugar. Prepared by culturing skim or low fat cows milk, resulting in a thickened, tangy yoghurt.

Name: Lamb, roasting cuts, fully-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw lamb from the three most common cuts used for roasting including leg roast, rack and round/topside roast. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. Majority of internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Tuna, canned in brine, drained
Description: Tuna flesh preserved by canning in brine, drained.

Name: Soy beverage, low fat (~ 0.5%), unflavoured, added Ca & vitamins A, B1, B2 & B12
Description: Beverage prepared from soy beans with a reduced fat content (~1.5%), purchased ready to drink. Contains added calcium, vitamins A, B1, B2 and B12.

Name: Chicken satay, Indonesian restaurant-style
Description: Pieces of chicken, grilled on wooden skewer, served with peanut sauce and garnished with parsley, tomato, cucumber and carrot, as served in Indonesian restaurants.

Name: Gluten, from wheat (vital wheat gluten)
Description: Protein rich extract of wheat flour.

Name: Taramosalata, dip, contains fish egg & bread
Description: Greek-style puree of fish roe, bread, oil, lemon juice and garlic as purchased from delicatessens.

Name: Lamb, all cuts, separable fat, cooked
Description: Cooked internal and external separable fat from 11 different cuts from various regions of the carcase. Oven roasted or grilled as purchased, still attached to the lean muscle meat, with no added fat to an internal temperature of 70C or until 'medium', then dissected.

Name: Cabbage, red, canned, heated, drained
Description: Large, smooth and round in shape, with layers of tightly packed purple-red coloured leaves. Canned in sweetened brine, heated in packing liquid, then drained.

Name: Beef, scotch fillet, fully-trimmed, grilled
Description: Cooked beef from the fore portion of the carcase. Grilled for 6-10 minutes until 'medium' with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Cauliflower, boiled, drained
Description: Tight white flower clusters which form the head, with a white stem. Cooked by boiling in unsalted water, then drained.

Name: Lamb, mini roast, separable lean, raw
Description: Raw lamb from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Sauce, tomato, no added salt, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared sauce with a thick consistency. Contains tomatoes, sugar, food acid and spices. No added salt.

Name: Pork, medallion or loin steak, separable fat, raw
Description: Raw internal and external separable fat from the midsection of the carcase.

Name: Biscuit, sweet, shortbread style, homemade
Description: Shortbread style biscuit, prepared in the home from common household ingredients including butter, flour, sugar and rice flour, baked.

Name: Beef satay, Vietnamese restaurant-style
Description: Beef, onion, capsicum and other vegetables, such as carrot, chilli, tomato, shallots or garlic, in satay sauce, as served in Vietnamese restaurants.

Name: Frankfurt, canned, heated, drained
Description: Canned frankfurt containing meat (including pork), skim milk powder, salt, potato starch, flavour enhancer, mineral salt, spices, sodium nitrite and water. Heated as per can instructions and drained.

Name: Garlic roll
Description: Processed and flavoured sandwich meat, commonly containing pork, mutton, meat, cereal, soy protein, milk protein, salt, sugar, herbs, spices, antioxidant, sodium nitrite and  water.

Name: Cordial base, 25% non-citrus fruit juice (apple & berry)
Description: Concentrated sugar-based syrup containing at least 25% non-citrus fruit juice (typically apple and berry juice), used to prepare a beverage by dilution with water.

Name: Pate de foie (chicken liver pate)
Description: Meat paste commonly containing chicken liver, pork, salt, herbs, spices, flavours, sodium nitrite, food acid and water.

Name: Beef, sirloin steak, semi-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw beef from the midsection of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. Majority of external fat removed.

Name: Breakfast cereal, oat bran
Description: Ingredients such as  oat bran, oats, rice, honey, wheatgerm, milk powder and nuts,  extruded into desired shapes.

Name: Ice cream, reduced fat, vanilla flavour
Description: Australian produced vanilla ice cream. Major ingredients include milk, sugar, gums and emulsifiers. Prepared by freezing rapidly with agitation to aerate the ice cream and give a light texture. Formulated to be reduced in fat compared to regular vanilla ice cream.

Name: Bread, from rye flour, light
Description: Commercially prepared bread made from rye flour, or including a large proportion of rye flour combined with wheat flour. It is a lighter, softer, milder flavoured bread than dark rye bread. Contains added folate and iodised salt. Ready to eat.

Name: Eggplant, raw
Description: A smooth, shiny deep purple-blackish skinned vegetable with a creamy white interior with many small light brown seeds dispersed through the flesh. Uncooked.

Name: Whiting, king george, flesh, raw
Description: Uncooked flesh of king george whiting.

Name: Mandarin, canned in syrup
Description: Mandarin orange segments canned in sugar syrup.

Name: Cheese, parmesan, shaved
Description: Parmesan-style cheese. Prepared by removing the majority of cream from cows milk before heating, curdling and brining. Cheese is shaved or coarsely grated prior to sale so that it is moister than finely grated parmesan cheese and requires refrigerator storage.

Name: Lamb, roasting cuts, semi-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw lamb from the three most common cuts used for roasting including leg roast, rack and round/topside roast. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. Majority of external fat removed.

Name: Lamb, tongue, raw
Description: Raw tongue including flesh and skin from a lamb.

Name: Breakfast cereal, whole wheat, biscuit, organic, added vitamins B1, B2 & B3
Description: Breakfast cereal made from organic whole wheat and added B1, B2 and B3- formed into the shape of a biscuit. Vita Brits is an example of such a product.

Name: Muffin, English style, from white flour, added dried fruit, toasted
Description: A round yeasted dough, baked on both sides (approximately 8 cm in diameter and 2 cm thick). Contains added dried fruit and spice. Contains added folate and iodised salt. Cooked by toasting after purchase until lightly brown.

Name: Persimmon, peeled, raw
Description: Round to heart shaped fruit with bright orange skin and orange flesh.

Name: Mushroom, common, stir-fried without oil
Description: Cultivated mushrooms that are cream in colour with brown gills, a rounded cap and thick stem. Vary in size and includes mushrooms described as button and flat. Cooked by stir-frying with out added oil.

Name: Chicken, drumstick, lean, casseroled
Description: Flesh from drumstick portion of a chicken. Skin removed. Cooked by baking in casserole dish with added water, then drained.

Name: Broccoli, fresh, microwaved
Description: Deep green flower clusters which form the head, and pale green stems. Cooked by microwaving from raw.

Name: Yoghurt, low fat (<0.5%), vanilla flavoured
Description: Australian produced yoghurt that is sweetened and flavoured with vanilla. Prepared by culturing low fat milk (less than 1% fat), resulting in a thickened, tangy yoghurt.

Name: Broccoli, fresh, raw
Description: Deep green flower clusters which form the head, and pale green stems. Uncooked.

Name: Soup, mixed vegetable, prepared from dry mix with water
Description: Vegetable soup prepared from dry soup mix mixed with water according to label instructions.

Name: Potato, pontiac, peeled, baked
Description: Round in shape, with a pink to red smooth skin and a creamy yellow flesh. Peeled and baked without added oil.

Name: Cordial base, 25% non-citrus fruit juice (apple & berry), intense sweetened
Description: Concentrated syrup containing at least 25% non-citrus fruit juice (typically apple and berry juice) and intense sweeteners, used to prepare a beverage by dilution with water.

Name: Flour, rice
Description: Flour ground from broken pieces and whole grains of medium grained milled rice.

Name: Pigeon (squab), whole, raw
Description: Raw meat from whole pigeon carcase, offal and bone removed.

Name: Lamb, souvlakia, Greek take-away
Description: Marinated lamb that has been cooked by grilling on a skewer, as served in Greek takeaway shops.

Name: Mayonnaise, reduced fat, commercial
Description: A white, emulsified sauce with a similar thick consistency to cream using lower levels of oil to develop a product with a reduced fat content. Used in sandwiches and to dress salads. Major ingredients include oil, sugar and vinegar.

Name: Loquat, peeled, raw
Description: Small round fruit, also known as Japanese Medlar- Nispero.

Name: Bacon, middle rasher, 75% trimmed, fried
Description: Cured, smoked and cooked pork middle rasher containing salt, sugar, mineral salts, antioxidant, nitrite and water. 75% of fat removed. Cooked by frying.

Name: Falafel, chickpea patty
Description: Chickpea based patty with herbs and spices, deep fried.

Name: Beef, fillet steak, untrimmed, grilled
Description: Cooked beef from the midsection of the carcase. Grilled for 6-10 minutes until 'medium' with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with internal and external fat attached.

Name: Peach, canned in light syrup
Description: Small stone fruit with a reddish/orange furry skin and orange flesh canned in light syrup.

Name: Pork, fillet, fully-trimmed, roasted
Description: Cooked lean pork from the loin region of the carcase. Oven roasted, as purchased with no separable fat, at 180C to an internal temperature of ~70C with no added fat.

Name: Coffee, instant, dry powder or granules, decaffeinated
Description: Dried extract of decaffeinated coffee beans, used to produce a beverage by the addition of boiling water.

Name: Pork, loin cutlet, as purchased, raw
Description: Raw pork from the midsection of the carcase, as purchased without removal of internal and external fat.

Name: Hummus dip, Lebanese restaurant-style
Description: Spread of ground chick peas, tahini, lemon juice, garlic and oil, as served in Lebanese restaurants.

Name: Lamb, loin chop, untrimmed, raw
Description: Raw lamb from the midsection of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal and external fat attached.

Name: Pork, forequarter chop, separable lean, raw
Description: Raw lean muscle meat from the forequarter of the carcase, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Kabana, processed meat
Description: Processed sausage type meat commonly made from pork, beef, salt, seasoning, antioxidant, sodium nitrite and water.

Name: Gelato, various flavours
Description: Australian produced flavoured gelato. Includes gelato described as strawberry, rockmelon, lemon, chocolate and may include a proportion of sponge cake or dried fruits. Contains milk products.

Name: Bread roll, from wholemeal flour
Description: Commercially prepared bread made from wholemeal, wheaten bread-making flour and other permitted ingredients. Dough is shaped into individual serves before baking. Contains added folate and iodised salt. Ready to eat.

Name: Pastry, puff, vegetable oil, commercial, baked
Description: Pastry purchased raw from supermarkets and then baked at approx 225 degrees C for 13 minutes. Produces a pastry that contains multiple fine layers and is often used on the top of pies. Typical ingredients include wheat flour, vegetable fat, salt, citric acid and preservative.

Name: Venison, stir fry strips, lean, dry fried
Description: Venison stir fry strips from the hind leg muscle of the carcase, with all visible fat removed. Dry fried for 2-3 minutes without the addition of oil until lightly browned and cooked through.

Name: Orange, valencia,  peeled, raw
Description: Round in shape with an orange thin waxy peel and orange flesh, that can be broken into segments.

Name: Veal, leg steak, separable lean, raw
Description: Raw veal from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Juice, orange, added calcium, & vitamins A, C & folate
Description: Commercial beverage prepared from the endocarp of navel oranges. Contains added vitamins A, C and folate and calcium. Does not contain added sucrose. Includes fresh and ultra heat treated products.

Name: Almond, milk chocolate-coated
Description: Almonds coated in a layer of milk chocolate.

Name: Salmon, Pacific king, fillets, flesh only, raw
Description: Uncooked, largely skinless fillets of fresh pacific king salmon, produced by aquaculture.

Name: Chicken, thigh fillets, lean & some fat, raw
Description: Raw flesh from the thigh area of chickens, removed from the bone and some adhering fat removed although some remains. As purchased from supermarkets.

Name: Cake mix, chocolate flavour, dry
Description: Commercially prepared dry chocolate flavoured cake mix. Typical ingredients may include sugar, wheat flour, cocoa, vegetable fats and sodium bicarbonates.

Name: Cheese, mozzarella
Description: Cheese made from cows milk and having a rubbery texture. Typically added to pizza and other Italian-style dishes.

Name: Beef, round steak, fully-trimmed, grilled
Description: Cooked beef from the hind portion of the carcase. Grilled for 6-10 minutes until 'medium' with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Breakfast cereal, wheat bran, pellets, added vitamins B1, B2 & folate, Fe, Mg & Zn
Description: Cereal made from wheat bran with added iron, B1, B2, zinc, magnesium and folate.

Name: Salt, flavoured
Description: Seasoning product that is primarily table salt to which various flavourings (such as celery, garlic, onion, herbs or chicken) are added.

Name: Cherry, glace or maraschino
Description: Cooked pitted cherries repeatedly covered in a sugar syrup and containing the red colour erythrosine. Eaten as a confection or used as a dessert ingredient, decoration or topping, or in cakes.

Name: Sauce, taco style, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared Mexican style spicy tomato-based sauce used for a topping on tacos. Commonly contains water, tomato, onion, capsicum, modified cornstarch, salt, pepper, vinegar, garlic, herbs, spices, food acid and jalapenos.

Name: Sugar, white, granulated or lump
Description: Purified extract from the sugar cane plant that is composed almost entirely of sucrose and may be supplied in lumps, coarse or fine granules or as a powder.

Name: Beer, ale
Description: Alcoholic beverage characterised by the presence of hops or preparations of hops, prepared by the yeast fermentation of an aqueous extract of malted or unmalted cereals (usually barley), using warm temperature fermentation. Approximately 5% v/v alcohol.

Name: Mineral water, with 5% citrus fruit juice
Description: Carbonated, non-alcoholic beverage containing 5% citrus juice (orange and lemon), mineral water and sugar.

Name: Beef, blade steak, semi-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw beef from the fore portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. All possible external fat removed.

Name: Bar, snack or breakfast style, cereal & milk solids
Description: A cereal and milk based snack-style breakfast bar. Major ingredients include puffed rice or breakfast cereal, sweetened condensed milk and skim milk powder, or milk filling.

Name: Skordalia, Greek restaurant-style
Description: Bread, potato, garlic and olive dip as served in Greek restaurants.

Name: Chicken burger, with mayonnaise & lettuce, fast food chain-style
Description: Commercially prepared crumbed chicken breast with mayonnaise and shredded lettuce in a white bun, as served in fast food style outlets.

Name: Chicken, breast, lean, raw
Description: Raw flesh from breast portion of the chicken. Skin removed.

Name: Pork, loin chop, separable fat, dry-fried
Description: Cooked internal and external separable fat from the lumbar part of loin. Dry-fried on BBQ plate.

Name: Lamb, chump chop, fully-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw lamb from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. Majority of internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Wine, white, medium dry style (~ 1% sugars)
Description: Alcoholic beverage prepared by fermentation of grape juice, with little contact with grape skins so that the wine is pale yellow in colour with some sugars remaining. Includes gewurztraminer and riesling grape varieties. Approximately 11% v/v alcohol.

Name: Grapefruit, peeled, raw
Description: Large, slightly tart citrus fruit. The rind is mostly yellow, and often tinged with green or red, with white pulp.

Name: Cheese, gouda
Description: Australian and imported cheese. Prepared by curdling cows milk with rennet, followed by curing.

Name: Mandarin, canned in syrup, syrup only
Description: Syrup made from water and sugar, used in canned mandarins.

Name: Custard apple, african pride, peeled, raw
Description: Light green to bluish green skin covered in irregular smooth bumps with white-cream flesh.

Name: Baking soda (bicarbonate), dry powder
Description: Fine white powder used to chemically leaven baked goods such as cakes.

Name: Tuna, flavoured, canned in oil, drained
Description: Tuna flesh canned in oil with added flavouring ingredients such as capsicum, chilli, vinegar, juice, tomato, onion, olives, herbs and spices and salt. Products vary in composition between brands.

Name: Pastry, spinach & cheese filled, commercial, ready to eat
Description: Commercially prepared savoury filo pastry product enclosing a filling of spinach and cheese (generally ricotta or feta), as purchased in bakeries or purchased frozen and reheated.

Name: Lamb, mini roast, fully-trimmed, roasted
Description: Cooked lamb from the hind portion of the carcase. Oven roasted to an internal temperature of 70C with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Wattle seed (acacia), ground
Description: Seeds of Acacia species, roasted, seed coats removed, ground, as supplied for culinary use.

Name: Polish sausage
Description: Salami containing pork, beef, salt, sugar, spices, sodium nitrite and sodium nitrate. Purchased ready to eat.

Name: Breakfast cereal, flakes of corn, added nuts, added vitamins B1, B2, B3, C & folate, Fe & Zn
Description: Breakfast cereal made from flakes of corn with added honey and nuts and vitamins C, B1, B2, B3 and folate, and the minerals iron and zinc.

Name: Beef, fillet steak, untrimmed, raw
Description: Raw beef from the midsection of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal and external fat attached.

Name: Beef, in black bean sauce, Chinese restaurant-style
Description: Beef, onion, capsicum and other vegetables such as bamboo shoots or carrot, cooked in black bean sauce, as served in Chinese restaurants.

Name: Vegetables & sausages, canned, heated
Description: Canned vegetable and meat product containing vegetables, broth, sausages (beef & pork), wheat flour, salt, mineral salt, spices, tomato paste, sugar, barley and water. Product prepared as per label instructions.

Name: Rice, white, raw
Description: Grain that has had its husk, bran and germ removed. The grains after milling have a slight off-white colour. Uncooked.

Name: Flour, wheat, wholemeal, plain
Description: Flour milled from whole wheat grain (bran, germ and flour). No added vitamins, minerals or leavening agents.

Name: Apple, pink lady, unpeeled, raw
Description: Round shaped fruit with pink/red skin and cream coloured flesh.

Name: Onion, pickled, drained, commercial
Description: Small onions in sweetened brine, with brine drained before consumption.

Name: Bean, green, fresh, boiled, drained
Description: Long, thin, green, crisp pod with small round smooth seeds inside. Trimmed, sliced, and boiled in unsalted water then drained.

Name: Ham, leg, lean & fat, canned
Description: Canned leg ham containing pork, gelatine, salt, mineral salt, agar, sugar, antioxidant, sodium nitrite and water.

Name: Beverage, chocolate flavour, from drinking chocolate, with regular fat milk
Description: Beverage prepared by mixing drinking chocolate powder with regular fat milk.

Name: Eggplant, grilled
Description: A smooth, shiny deep purple-blackish skinned vegetable with a creamy white interior with many small light brown seeds dispersed through the flesh. Cooked by grilling.

Name: Beef, stir-fry cuts, fully-trimmed, cooked
Description: Cooked beef from the three most common cuts used for stir-frying including round steak, topside steak and rump steak. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. Majority of internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Hamburger, beef pattie, with cheese, lettuce, onion & sauce, takeaway style
Description: Commercially prepared fried meat patty with sliced processed cheese, lettuce, tomato, onion and tomato sauce in a white bun as purchased in independent take-away food outlets.

Name: Salmon, raw, sashimi style, Japanese restaurant-style
Description: Thin slices of raw salmon as purchased from Japanese style restaurants

Name: Salami, pepperoni
Description: Spicy, fermented manufactured meat, served in thin circular slices. Product contains pork and beef, salt, sugar, spices, sodium nitrate and sodium nitrite.

Name: Spread, yeast, marmite
Description: Very thick, dark brown spread. Concentrated yeast extract. Contains added salt, thiamin, riboflavin and niacin.

Name: Salami, milano
Description: Processed fermented sweet meat, served in circular slices. Contains pork, beef, salt, sugar, spices, sodium nitrate and sodium nitrite.

Name: Potato, coliban, peeled, mashed with milk and butter
Description: Round in shape, with a smooth whitish skin. Peeled and boiled in unsalted water, then drained and mashed with milk and butter.

Name: Potato, coliban, peeled, raw
Description: Round in shape, with a smooth whitish skin. Peeled. Uncooked.

Name: Pastry, shortcrust style, commercial, raw
Description: Uncooked pastry purchased in thin sheets or blocks from supermarkets. Produces a firm pastry often used on the base of pies. Typical ingredients include wheat flour, vegetable fat, glycerol, citric acid and water.

Name: Beef, topside steak, semi-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw beef from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. Majority of external fat removed.

Name: Shark (flake), skinless fillet, crumbed, fried, peanut oil
Description: Flesh from various types of shark (typically Gummy, School and Black Tipped shark). Commonly known as flake. Cooked by coating in white wheat flour, egg and commercial breadcrumbs and shallow frying in peanut oil. Crumb is 10% of uncooked product weight.

Name: Bean, haricot, dried, boiled, drained
Description: Small white beans oval in shape, dried beans soaked overnight, boiled in unsalted water, drained.

Name: Salami, unspecified variety
Description: Processed fermented meat, served in circular slices. Commonly contains pork, beef, salt, spices, sugar and sodium nitrate/sodium nitrite.

Name: Cordial, non-citrus fruit juice, intense sweetened, recommended dilution
Description: Non-alcoholic beverage prepared by mixing 1 part of a concentrated fruit-juice based syrup, sweetened with intense sweeteners rather than sugar, with 4 parts of water.

Name: Potato, new, peeled, mashed with milk & butter
Description: Immature potatoes, small and round in shape with a flimsy, parchment-like skin. Peeled and cooked by boiling in unsalted water, then drained and mashed with butter and milk.

Name: Coffee, from ground coffee beans, Turkish style, without milk
Description: Beverage produced by boiling ground coffee beans with water and sugar, as served in Turkish-style restaurants.

Name: Veal, kidney, grilled
Description: Kidney trimmed of fat and core, sliced and grilled.

Name: Biscuit, sweet, Anzac style
Description: Commercially prepared sweet crunchy oat based biscuit. Typical ingredients include rolled oats, wheat flour, coconut and golden syrup.

Name: Raspberry, raw
Description: Fresh unprocessed round berries characterised by a collection of tiny, shiny red drupelets.

Name: Flour, wheat, white, self-raising
Description: Flour prepared from ground wheat from which bran has been removed. Chemical leavening agents added. No added vitamins or minerals.

Name: Bacon, breakfast rasher, grilled
Description: Cured, smoked and cooked pork rasher produced from chopped and reformed meat and containing salt, sugar, mineral salts, antioxidant, nitrite and water.  Cooked by grilling.

Name: Wine, white, dry style (sugars content < 1%)
Description: Fermented grape juice produced with little contact with grape skins so that the wine is pale yellow in colour with little sugars remaining. Includes wine described as white burgundy, or produced from chardonnay, semillon, colombard, chenin blanc and tokay varieties. Approximately 12% v/v alcohol.

Name: Lamb, roasting cuts, semi-trimmed, cooked
Description: Cooked lamb from the three most common cuts used for roasting including leg roast, rack and round/topside roast. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. Majority of external fat removed after cooking.

Name: Biscuit, savoury, from white flour, water cracker style
Description: Commercially prepared round, savoury biscuits made from white wheat flour, some with added cracked pepper.

Name: Potato, desiree, peeled, boiled
Description: Round in shape, with a pink to red smooth skin and a creamy yellow flesh. Peeled and boiled in unsalted water, then drained.

Name: Soft drink, orange flavour
Description: Carbonated, non-alcoholic beverage prepared from water, sugar, orange flavour and colours.

Name: Barramundi, aquacultured, fillets, raw
Description: Uncooked fillets of barramundi, produced under aquaculture and imported into Australia.

Name: Chocolate, milk, sugar-coated
Description: Confectionery product comprised of milk chocolate covered with a sugar-based coating and shaped into a small disc or ball. Includes products described as Smarties.

Name: Cabbage, mustard, raw
Description: Plant with thick, pale green, grooved, curving stems with a small fringe of deeper green leaf along the edges and across the top of stems. Uncooked.

Name: Guava, hawaiian, raw
Description: Round to oblong shaped green skinned tropical fruit with pink flesh.

Name: Biscuit, savoury, from rye flour, crispbread
Description: A thin, flat rectangle of dry bread made predominantly from rye flour, including lite varieties (e.g. Ryvita style). Commercially prepared- some brands may include a proportion of wheat flour.

Name: Beef, mince, low fat (lean/heart smart), dry fried (2008)
Description: Minced beef supplied with a fat content of around 8%, cooked by frying without added fat. Includes minced beef labelled as lean, heart smart, five star, choice or extra lean.

Name: Liqueur, advocaat
Description: Alcoholic beverage prepared from brandy and egg yolks.

Name: Silver perch, aquacultured, steamed or poached
Description: Fillets of silver perch produced in Australia by aquaculture. Cooked by steaming or poaching.

Name: Snapper, flesh, grilled or barbecued, brushed with olive oil
Description: Fillets of silver perch produced in Australia by aquaculture. Cooked by grilling or barbecuing on a hotplate after first brushing with olive oil.

Name: Ham, shoulder, lean & fat, canned
Description: Canned shoulder ham containing pork, salt, gelatine, mineral salt, agar, sugar, antioxidant, sodium erythorbate, sodium nitrite, sodium phosphate and water.

Name: Gnocchi, potato, commercially prepared, boiled
Description: Commercially prepared dumplings made from potato and wheat flour, simmered briefly in boiling water.

Name: Chicken, wing, lean, skin & fat, casseroled
Description: Flesh, skin and separable fat from the wing portion of a chicken. Cooked by baking in a casserole dish with added water, then drained.

Name: Flour, rye, wholemeal
Description: A flour made from the milled wholegrain of rye.

Name: Biscuit, sweet, chocolate chip & nut
Description: Commercially prepared sweet biscuits with added chocolate chips and nuts.

Name: Breadcrumbs, white, commercial
Description: Crisp crumbs crushed from thiamin fortified white bread which has been dried and packaged before sale. Contains added iodised salt.

Name: Beetroot, fresh, peeled, boiled, drained
Description: Rounded root vegetable with dark brown-purple skin and stems and purple flesh.  Flesh boiled in unsalted water then drained.

Name: Juice, vegetable blend, tomato, carrot, celery & parsley, added salt
Description: Commercial beverage prepared from tomato, carrot, celery, parsley and other vegetable juices. Contains added salt, but no added sugar.

Name: Capsicum, green, stir-fried without oil
Description: A shiny green vegetable with crisp, moist flesh. Hollow with a seeded core. Chopped and stir-fried without added oil.

Name: Veal, cutlet, fully-trimmed, grilled
Description: Cooked veal from the midsection of the carcase. Grilled for 6-10 minutes until 'medium' with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Chives, raw
Description: Long, thin, flattish, dark green stem which comes to a point at the top. Uncooked.

Name: Doughnut, cream or custard filled
Description: Batter shaped into a ball, deep fried. A small amount of cream or custard is then injected into the centre of the cooked doughnut.

Name: Potato crisps or chips, plain, reduced fat, salted
Description: Snack product that consists of thinly sliced potato, deep fried in vegetable oil, salted & packaged. Does not contain any added flavours. Product formulated to be reduced in fat compared with regular potato crisps.

Name: Beer, bitter
Description: Alcoholic beverage characterised by the presence of hops or preparations of hops, prepared by the yeast fermentation of an aqueous extract of malted or unmalted cereals (usually barley), and described on the label as bitter style. Approximately 3.9% v/v alcohol.

Name: Soft drink, lemon flavour
Description: Carbonated, non-alcoholic beverage prepared from water, sugar, lemon flavour and colours.

Name: Chicken, breast, lean, grilled
Description: Flesh from breast portion of a chicken. Skin removed. Cooked by grilling without addition of oil.

Name: Tapioca, pearl or seed style, raw
Description: Starchy product from the cassava plant supplied in the form of small pellets (also known as seeds or pearls). Sometimes sold labelled as Sago tapioca or Sago. Imported into Australia. Uncooked.

Name: Biscuit, sweet, chocolate chip
Description: Commercially prepared sweet biscuits with added chocolate chips.

Name: Cheese, cheddar, reduced fat (~25%)
Description: Cheddar cheese prepared by curdling cows milk with rennet, followed by curing. Supplied with a fat content of approximately 25%.

Name: Pork, in plum sauce, Chinese restaurant-style
Description: Pork and vegetables such as cabbage or pineapple, cooked in a plum sauce, as served in Chinese restaurants.

Name: Lady finger (pastry with vegetables), Lebanese restaurant-style
Description: Filo pastry stuffed with spinach and onion, as served in Lebanese restaurants.

Name: Passionfruit, raw
Description: Pulp and seeds of purple skinned passionfruit.

Name: Chicken, thigh, lean, casseroled
Description: Flesh from thigh portion of a chicken. Skin removed. Cooked by baking in a casserole dish with added water, then drained.

Name: Pork, leg steak (round, rump, topside, silverside), as purchased, raw
Description: Raw pork from 4 cuts (round, rump, topside and silverside) from the hind portion of the carcase, as purchased without removal of internal and external fat.

Name: Peanut butter, smooth & crunchy, no added sugar or salt
Description: Paste made from roasted, unsalted and ground peanuts. Available in two types with (crunchy) and with out (smooth) chunks of peanuts. Does not contain added salt or sugar.

Name: Veal, leg roast, fully-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw veal from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. Majority of internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Potato, new, peeled, raw
Description: Immature potatoes, small and round in shape with a flimsy, parchment-like skin. Peeled. Uncooked.

Name: Pastry mix, commercial, prepared from dry mix with water, baked
Description: Pastry prepared from packaged pastry mix by the addition of water, followed by baking.

Name: Artichoke, globe, raw
Description: The unopened flower bud of a thistle with gold-green to purple coloured leaves surrounding a hairy inedible choke, on top of an edible heart. Round to conical in shape. Edible portion comprises lower part of leaves and heart.

Name: Cornmeal (polenta), cooked in water, with added salt
Description: A type of flour ground from dried kernels of yellow or white corn. Cooked by boiling in unsalted water without the addition of fat or oil.

Name: Milk, cow, fluid, regular fat (~3.5%)
Description: The mammary secretion of milking animals, obtained from one or more milking for consumption as liquid milk or for further processing, excluding colostrum, prepared for consumption by pasteurisation and homogenisation. Milk contains a minimum of 3.2 g milk fat/100 g.

Name: Lettuce, iceberg, raw
Description: Round in shape, with packed layers of crisp green leaves. Uncooked.

Name: Fruit drink, 30% orange & 5% mango juices, added vitamin C
Description: Commercially prepared beverage made from 35% fruit juice (>30% orange juice and <5% mango juice or puree), water and sugars. Contains added vitamin C.

Name: Pineapple (cayenne), peeled, raw
Description: Oval fruit with a thick greenish skin and yellow flesh. Cayenne variety. Skin removed.

Name: Bread, flat (pita or Lebanese), wholemeal
Description: Double layered, Middle Eastern style flat bread made from wholemeal wheat flour with a small amount of crumb adhering to both crusts. May vary in diameter. Contains added folate, iodised salt and thiamin.

Name: Sherbet
Description: Sugar based confectionery, flavoured powder with food acid. Also contains sodium bicarbonate, magnesium carbonate and flavours and colours.

Name: Nectarine, unpeeled, raw
Description: Small stone fruit with a reddish/orange skin and orange flesh.

Name: Cheese, cheddar, reduced fat (~ 15%)
Description: Cheddar cheese prepared by curdling cows milk with rennet, followed by curing. Supplied with a fat content of approximately 15%.

Name: Marmalade, orange
Description: A sugary fruit preserve with a lumpier consistency than jam as both the skin and pulp of the orange is used in its making.

Name: Margarine, polyunsaturated
Description: A polyunsaturated edible oil spread containing no less than 80% edible oils. Contains added salt and vitamins A and D.

Name: Tabouleh, Lebanese restaurant-style
Description: A Lebanese style salad typically containing a mixture of parsley, bulgur, mint, tomato, onion, oil, a pinch of cinnamon and lemon juice, as purchased in Lebanese restaurants.

Name: Beef, silverside roast, separable lean, raw
Description: Raw beef from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Pikelet, homemade
Description: Home prepared batter, made from self-raising wheat flour, milk, egg and sugar, spooned onto a buttered hotplate and cooked until batter is set.

Name: Water, bottled, still
Description: Water, other than mineral water, bottled prior to sale. May include spring water.

Name: Pork, loin chop, separable lean, raw
Description: Raw lean muscle meat from the loin portion of the carcase, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Veal, loin chop, untrimmed, raw
Description: Raw veal from the midsection of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal and external fat attached.

Name: Bread, Roti, Indian restaurant style
Description: Flat, Indian style bread as prepared from wholewheat flour and purchased in Indian-style restaurants. Baked or fried with added fat. Ready to eat.

Name: Beef, fillet steak, separable lean, grilled
Description: Cooked beef from the midsection of the carcase. Grilled for 6-10 minutes until 'medium' with no added fat. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Orange, navel (leng),  peeled, raw
Description: Round seedless orange with small to medium sized yellow/orange fruit and smooth textured thin rind.

Name: Chocolate, milk, fondant or caramel filled
Description: Confectionery product comprised of a milk chocolate exterior enclosing a soft caramel or fondant cream type filling. Includes chocolates such as Snack or Caramello.

Name: Beer, low alcohol (<1% alcohol v/v)
Description: Alcoholic beverage characterised by the presence of hops or preparations of hops, prepared by the yeast fermentation of an aqueous extract of malted or unmalted cereals (usually barley), so as to restrict alcohol formation or to remove alcohol after fermentation. Products are described on label as Special/Ultra/Extra Light. Approximately 0.7% v/v alcohol.

Name: Beer, stout
Description: Alcoholic beverage characterised by the presence of hops or preparations of hops, prepared by the yeast fermentation of an aqueous extract of malted or unmalted cereals (usually barley), so that it is dark coloured. Approximately 5.7% v/v alcohol.

Name: Snapper, flesh, steamed
Description: Fillets of snapper flesh, cooked by steaming.

Name: Mullet, yelloweye, steamed
Description: Fillets and possible skin of mullet caught in Australian waters. Cooked by steaming.

Name: Whiting, king george, flesh, steamed
Description: Flesh of king george whiting, cooked by steaming.

Name: Beverage base, meal replacement powder, chocolate flavour, added nutrients
Description: Chocolate flavoured dry beverage base, which is intended to be mixed with milk or water and consumed in place of a regular meal. Typical ingredients include sugar, milk solids, inulin, cocoa and up to 24 added vitamins and minerals

Name: Flour, wheat, white, plain
Description: Flour prepared from ground wheat from which bran has been removed. No added vitamins or minerals.

Name: Fruit salad, canned in heavy syrup, drained
Description: A variety of fruits that have been canned in a heavy sugar based syrup, then drained.

Name: Juice, orange, home squeezed
Description: Homemade beverage prepared from freshly squeezed oranges.

Name: Pizza, cheese & pesto, purchased frozen, uncooked
Description: Commercially produced pizza dough topped with cheese and pesto, frozen before packaging. Uncooked.

Name: Lamb, leg roast, fully-trimmed, roasted
Description: Cooked lamb from the hind portion of the carcase. Oven roasted to an internal temperature of 70C with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Salad, potato, commercial
Description: A salad typically containing cooked potato and a dressing made from mayonnaise, and other ingredients such as dill, lemon juice, garlic, salt and ground black pepper.

Name: Squash, scallopini, boiled, drained
Description: Small, rounded vegetable fruit, generally with a green skin. Cooked by boiling in unsalted water, then drained.

Name: Marshmallow, plain or flavoured
Description: Confectionery style produced made from sugar or corn syrup, water, gelatine that has been pre-softened in hot water, dextrose, and flavourings, whipped to a spongy consistency.

Name: Raspberry, purchased frozen
Description: Raw round berries characterised by a collection of tiny, shiny red drupelets. Frozen prior to sale.

Name: Lasagne (lasagna), beef, Italian restaurant- style
Description: Commercially produced minced beef and tomato filling in pasta layers with white sauce and cheese as purchased from Italian restaurants.

Name: Beef, extract, bonox
Description: Concentrated beef extract rich in iron, niacin and folate. Thick dark brown liquid paste added to soups or stews for flavouring or to hot water for a salty beverage.

Name: Mutton, all cuts, separable fat, raw
Description: Raw mutton fat from various regions of the carcase. Internal and external separable fat only.

Name: Pork, leg steak (round, rump, topside, silverside), as purchased, dry fried
Description: Cooked pork from 4 cuts (round, rump, topside and silverside) from the hind portion of the carcase, as purchased without removal of internal and external separable fat. Dry fried to an internal temperature of ~70C with a small amount of pork fat.

Name: Beef, rump steak, separable lean, raw
Description: Raw beef from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Tomato, paste, with added salt
Description: A thick red paste made from tomatoes with added salt.

Name: Hamburger, beef pattie, with fried egg, lettuce, onion & sauce, takeaway style
Description: Commercially prepared fried meat patty with fried egg, lettuce, tomato, onion and tomato sauce in a white bun as purchased in independent take-away food outlets.

Name: Baked beans, canned in tomato sauce
Description: Navy/haricot beans in tomato sauce, canned. Contains added salt, sugar, food acids, maize thickener and flavour.

Name: Pork, forequarter shoulder roast, as purchased, raw
Description: Raw pork from the forequarter of the carcase, as purchased without removal of internal and external fat.

Name: Lentil, dried, boiled, drained
Description: Dried green, red and brown lentils soaked, boiled in unsalted water, then drained.

Name: Silver perch, aquacultured, raw
Description: Uncooked fillets of silver perch produced in Australia by aquaculture.

Name: Chicken, thigh, lean, skin & fat, casseroled
Description: Flesh, skin and separable fat from the thigh portion of a chicken. Cooked by baking in a casserole dish with added water, then drained.

Name: Pork, strips, as purchased, stir-fried
Description: Cooked lean pork strips, as purchased, likely to be from leg or shoulder steak.  Dry fried to an internal temperature of ~75C with a small amount of pork fat.

Name: Lamb, easy carve shoulder, semi-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw lamb from the fore portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. Majority of external fat removed.

Name: Sausage roll, commercial, ready to eat, individual size
Description: Commercially prepared meat filling (usually beef and/or lamb) rolled in pastry, ready to eat.

Name: Bread, mixed grain
Description: Commercially prepared bread made from white and or wholemeal flour with added kibbled grains. Contains added folate, iodised salt and thiamin. Ready to eat.

Name: Liqueur, cream-based, coffee flavour
Description: Coffee flavoured alcoholic beverage mixed with dairy cream.

Name: Scallop, raw
Description: Flesh and roe of uncooked scallop.

Name: Cheese, neufchatel
Description: Prepared by the addition of rennet and culture to pasteurised cows milk, producing a soft, unripened cheese.

Name: Beef, fillet steak, fully-trimmed, grilled
Description: Cooked beef from the midsection of the carcase. Grilled for 6-10 minutes until 'medium' with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Grape, black sultana, raw
Description: Oval, black, seedless grapes with crisp texture.

Name: Wine, white, medium sweet style (~ 2.5% sugars)
Description: Alcoholic beverage prepared by fermentation of grape juice produced with little contact with grape skins so that the wine is pale yellow in colour, with some sugars remaining (approximately 2.5% sugars). Includes wine described as being moselle, liebfrauwine or spaetlese, or made from riesling or frontignac grape varieties. Approximately 10% v/v alcohol.

Name: Flour, arrowroot
Description: Flour ground from the starchy roots of a number of plants.

Name: Coconut, fresh, young or immature, flesh
Description: Flesh or meat from inside the immature coconut, not preserved by drying or other techniques.

Name: Pastry, shortcrust, wholemeal, commercial, raw
Description: Pastry purchased in thin sheets or blocks from supermarkets, ready for cooking. Produces a firm pastry often used on the base of pies. Typical ingredients include wholemeal wheat flour, vegetable fat, ascorbic acid, citric acid and water.

Name: Celery, raw
Description: A green upright vegetable with long stems and green leafy ends.

Name: Mixed fruit, dried
Description: Mixture of various types of dried fruits. Primarily sultanas and also including currants, citrus peel, raisins, cherries.

Name: Flour, wheat, white, self-raising, added calcium & folate
Description: Flour prepared from ground wheat from which bran has been removed. Chemical leavening agents added. Also contains added folate and calcium.

Name: Potato, chips, regular, par-fried in canola oil, purchased frozen, baked without oil
Description: Potato chips, par-fried in canola oil and purchased frozen. Heated by baking without added oil in an oven until golden brown.

Name: Spinach, frozen, boiled, drained
Description: Leafy vegetable with vivid crinkled green leaves on fine stem. Chopped spinach boiled in unsalted water, then drained.

Name: Pikelet, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared pancake. Typical ingredients include wheat flour and starch, sugar, salt, vegetable oil, skim milk powder, preservatives, thiamin, water, flavours and emulsifiers. Contains added folate.

Name: Doughnut, glazed
Description: Sweet dough made from yeast, water, milk, sugar, butter, flour, and eggs that is extruded into a ring shape and deep fried in oil. Covered in a glazed coating.

Name: Pork, medallion or loin steak, separable fat, dry fried
Description: Cooked internal and external separable fat from the midsection of the carcase. Dry fried, as purchased, to an internal temperature of ~70C with a small of pork fat, then dissected.

Name: Pork, topside steak, as purchased, dry fried
Description: Cooked pork from the hind portion of the carcase, as purchased without removal of internal and external separable fat. Dry fried to an internal temperature of ~70C with a small amount of pork fat.

Name: Dairy or yoghurt dessert, chocolate, child's product
Description: Commercially prepared, dairy product flavoured with chocolate and intended for use as a child's dessert. Typical ingredients include milk, sugar, cocoa, vegetable gums, salt, thickeners, emulsifiers and flavours.

Name: Spaghetti in meat sauce, canned
Description: Commercially prepared canned pasta product containing spaghetti in tomato-based meat sauce. Includes spaghetti bolognese and spaghetti and meat ball varieties.

Name: Soup, tomato & noodle, cup of soup, instant dry mix
Description: Instant tomato and noodle soup dry mix containing ingredients such as tomato powder, pasta, wheat gluten, beverage whitener, vegetable oil, antioxidants, maize starch, maltodextrin, salt and  spices. Requires dilution before consumption.

Name: Beef, diced, untrimmed, dry fried
Description: Cooked beef, purchased diced and likely to be from various regions of the carcase. Dry fried for 3-5 minutes with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with internal and external fat attached.

Name: Omelette, chicken, Chinese restaurant-style
Description: Egg, chicken, bean sprouts and other vegetables such as peas, with sauce.  Purchased ready-to-eat from Chinese restaurants.

Name: Beef, topside steak, fully-trimmed, roasted
Description: Cooked beef from the hind portion of the carcase. Oven roasted to an internal temperature of 70C with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Sugar, brown
Description: A soft moist brown sugar with a fine crystal size.

Name: Soup, vegetable, with noodle, simmer dry mix
Description: Dry vegetable and noodle simmer soup mix vegetables such as onion, carrot, tomato and peas, noodles, milk solids, vegetable oil, gums, maltodextrin, salt and antioxidants. intended for the preparation of a soup by mixing with water and simmering for several minutes.

Name: Scallop, boiled, unsalted water
Description: Flesh and roe of uncooked scallop heated in unsalted water until boiling point reached, then drained.

Name: Mutton, casserole, separable lean, casseroled
Description: Cooked lamb from the fore portion (shoulder) of the carcase. Browned, simmered in minimal water for 2 hours then drained. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Cordial, 25% citrus fruit juice, recommended dilution
Description: Non-alcoholic beverage prepared by mixing 1 part of a concentrated sugar syrup containing 25% citrus fruit juice with 4 parts of water.

Name: Chocolate, milk, with dried fruit & nut
Description: Confectionery product composed of milk chocolate with embedded dried fruit (typically sultanas) and nuts (typically cashews, hazelnuts or almonds).

Name: Lamb, stir-fry strips, separable lean, raw
Description: Raw lamb, purchased as strips and likely to be from various regions of the carcase. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Bar, muesli, plain or with dried fruit, chocolate-coated
Description: Snack style bar whose major ingredients include rolled oats, sugars, vegetable oil, puffed rice, dried fruit or fruit juice, nuts and seeds. The bar is covered or topped with chocolate.

Name: Pear, nashi, unpeeled, raw
Description: Appearance and size similar to that of an apple. Nashi pears have a smooth, green-yellow or brownish-russet skin depending on variety, and a crisp texture.

Name: Bread, from white flour, added iron
Description: Commercially prepared bread made from white, wheaten bread-making flour and other permitted ingredients. Contains added iron salts, folate, iodised salt and thiamin. Ready to eat.

Name: Wine, white, sparkling
Description: Alcoholic beverage prepared by fermentation of grape juice produced with little grape skin contact so that the wine is pale yellow in colour and retains significant quantities of dissolved carbon dioxide. Includes wine described as brut or semi-brut in style. Approximately 11% v/v alcohol.

Name: Sprout, bean, raw
Description: Sprouted from mung bean seeds. Long translucent to white in colour, with a short tapering green sheathed root. Uncooked.

Name: Bun sweet, with dried fruit, iced (finger bun)
Description: Commercially prepared sweet bun based on yeasted wheat flour dough and containing added dried fruit, topped with sugar based icing. Typical ingredients include bread making flour, dried fruit, sugar, fats, yeast, salt, spice, gums, water and leavening. Contains added folate and iodised salt. Includes products described as Finger Buns.

Name: Pineapple, fresh, cooked in light syrup, drained
Description: Oval fruit with a thick greenish skin and yellow flesh. Leaves, skin, bracts and core removed, then cooked in light syrup until boiling and the simmered for another 5 minutes until tender.

Name: Chicken chop suey, Chinese restaurant-style
Description: Chicken and vegetables such as cabbage, broccoli, carrot or bean sprouts, as served in Chinese restaurants.

Name: Cordial base, 40% non-citrus fruit juice (apple & berry)
Description: Concentrated sugar-based syrup containing at least 40% non-citrus fruit juice (typically apple and berry juice), used to prepare a beverage by dilution with water.

Name: Beef, silverside roast, separable lean, roasted without oil or fat
Description: Cooked beef from the hind portion of the carcase. Oven roasted to an internal temperature of 70C with no added fat. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Pizza, supreme, thin base, fast food chain style
Description: Commercially produced thin pizza dough topped with tomato-based sauce, cheese, ground beef, mushrooms, onion, capsicum and pepperoni. Purchased ready to eat from fast food outlets.

Name: Trout, rainbow, aquacultured, steamed or poached
Description: Pieces of rainbow trout (including some skin), produced in Australia by aquaculture. Cooked by steaming or poaching.

Name: Flour, soya, low fat
Description: Creamy, finely ground flour processed from soya beans, reduced in fat compared to regular soya flour.

Name: Beef, sirloin steak, semi-trimmed, grilled
Description: Cooked beef from the midsection of the carcase. Grilled for 6-10 minutes until 'medium' with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. Majority of external fat removed after cooking.

Name: Lamb, stir-fry strips, fully-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw lamb, purchased as strips and likely to be from various regions of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Bread roll, from white flour
Description: Commercially prepared bread made from white, wheaten bread-making flour and other permitted ingredients. Dough is shaped into individual serves before baking. Contains added folate and iodised salt. Ready to eat.

Name: Beef, stir-fry cuts, fully-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw beef from the three most common cuts used for stir-frying including round steak, topside steak and rump steak. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. Majority of internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Nut, cashew, raw
Description: Raw, cream coloured kidney shaped nuts, unsalted.

Name: Peach, unpeeled, raw
Description: Small stone fruit with a reddish/orange furry skin and orange flesh.

Name: Milk, cow, fluid, reduced fat (~1.5%), increased protein (~4%)
Description: Australian produced reduced fat cows milk. Supplied with fat content <2% and protein content ~4%.

Name: Breakfast cereal, whole wheat, small biscuit, added vitamins B1, B2, B3 & folate
Description: Breakfast cereal made from whole wheat, with added vitamins B1, B2, B3 and folate and shaped into small biscuits.

Name: Biscuit, sweet, Anzac style, homemade
Description: Crunchy oat biscuit prepared in the home. Made from common household ingredients including rolled oats, wheat flour, coconut and golden syrup.

Name: Sauce, white, savoury, made with reduced fat milk & margarine spread, homemade
Description: Home prepared creamy style sauce made in the home from margarine spread, white wheat flour and reduced fat milk.

Name: Starch, potato
Description: Fine powder composed of polysaccharides derived from the potato tuber.

Name: Avocado, raw
Description: Almost pear shaped, with a green to black shiny skin and a delicate yellow flesh with a green outer hue.

Name: Guacamole, avocado dip
Description: A dip typically containing avocado, lemon juice, chilli, onion, coriander, salt and pepper.

Name: Salt, rock
Description: A type of table salt that is predominantly sodium chloride but may contain a number of other minerals.

Name: Shark (flake), skinless fillet, battered, deep fried, tallow based fat
Description: Flesh from various types of shark (typically Gummy, School and Black Tipped shark). Commonly known as flake. Cooked by coating in white wheat flour-based batter containing salt and deep frying in tallow based fat. Batter is 22% of uncooked product weight.

Name: Beef, chuck steak, fully-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw beef from the fore portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Dhal (legume curry), Indian restaurant-style
Description: Legume curry, typically containing pigeon pea, black lentil in the skin, onion, ginger, cumin seeds, curry and coriander leaves and tomato, as served in Indian restaurants.

Name: Celeriac, peeled, boiled, drained
Description: A thick tuberous root with brown skin and white flesh, with a celery like flavour. Peeled, chopped, boiled in water, drained.

Name: Lamb, kibbi (meat & burghul), fried, Lebanese restaurant-style
Description: Egg-shaped balls, typically containing bulgur, meat and pine nuts, then deep-fried, as served in Lebanese restaurants.

Name: Ice cream, regular fat, vanilla with confectionery, with waffle cone, chocolate coated
Description: Australian produced frozen ice confection consisting of vanilla ice cream in a waffle cone with chocolate coating inside the cone and on top of the ice cream and sugar coated chocolate pieces spread throughout the ice cream. Cornetto and Drumstick with added confectionary pieces (e.g. Smarties) are examples of this style of product.

Name: Mullet, yelloweye, battered, deep fried, tallow based fat
Description: Fillets and possible skin of mullet, coated in white wheat flour-based batter containing added salt. Cooked by deep frying in tallow-based fat, then drained. Batter is 35% of the uncooked product.

Name: Oyster, smoked, canned in oil, drained
Description: Oyster flesh preserved by smoking and canning in edible oil (generally cottonseed oil) and salt. Drained of excess oil.

Name: Egg, duck, whole, boiled
Description: Edible portion, including yolk and white (albumen) of the egg of ducks, cooked by boiling in water.

Name: Brawn
Description: Jellied meat mixture, also known as presswurst. Commonly contains pork, but may also contain chicken. Other ingredients include vinegar, spices, salt, thickener (gelatine), cereal, soy protein, sugars, antioxidant, mineral salts, sodium nitrate and water.

Name: Soy beverage, regular fat (~ 3%), unflavoured, added Ca, vitamins A, B1, B2 & B12
Description: Beverage prepared from soy beans, purchased ready to drink. Contains added calcium and vitamins A, B1, B2 and B12.

Name: Fruit drink, 25% apple juice
Description: Commercially prepared product made from 25% apple juice or puree, water, sugars and food acids.

Name: Cake, chocolate, iced, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared rich chocolate flavoured cake. Contains chocolate icing topping. Includes cakes commonly described as mud cakes.

Name: Milk, powder, goat, regular
Description: Australian and imported goats milk powder.

Name: Beef, blade steak, separable lean, raw
Description: Raw beef from the fore portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Bagel, from white flour, toasted
Description: A ring of baked yeast dough with a chewy centre and a crusty outside. It is typically 8-10cm in diameter. Usually poached in water or steamed before being baked. Contains added folate and iodised salt. Cooked by toasting after purchase.

Name: Egg, chicken, yolk, hard-boiled
Description: Yolk portion of chicken eggs, separated from the white portion after boiled in shell in unsalted water for 7 minutes until both yolk and white were firm. Yolk separated from white prior to analysis.

Name: Cake, plain, prepared from dry mix, uniced
Description: Vanilla flavoured cake prepared from a vanilla cake dry mix, with the addition of eggs, regular fat milk, margarine spread and water, then baked. Ingredients for preparation vary depending on cake mix brand.

Name: Noodle snack , wheat, flavoured, dry
Description: Dry noodles made from pregelatinised wheat starch and eaten as a snack.

Name: Veal, leg steak, fully-trimmed,  grilled
Description: Cooked veal from the hind portion of the carcase. Grilled for 6-10 minutes until 'medium' with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Beef, rump steak, semi-trimmed, grilled (2008)
Description: Cooked beef from the hind portion of the carcase. Grilled until 'medium' with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. Majority of external fat removed after cooking.

Name: Asparagus, boiled
Description: Long crisp stem with a fragile feathery tip boiled in water and then drained. Usually green in colour.

Name: Muesli, toasted, with added dried fruit & nut
Description: Breakfast cereal made from rolled oats, dried fruit and other ingredients such as nuts, coconut and seeds, and then toasted with the addition of vegetable oil.

Name: Sardine, canned in oil
Description: Sardines preserved by salting and canning in edible oil.

Name: Cheese, cream
Description: Soft, white cheese prepared by blending, culturing and salting cows milk, cream and vegetable gum.

Name: Cherry, black, canned in syrup
Description: Small black  cherries canned in sugar syrup.

Name: Prickly pear, peeled, raw
Description: Smooth skinned cactus fruit with clusters of tiny hairlike spines, pulpy flesh containing numerous small black seeds. Also known as Indian Fig- Mission Cactus.

Name: Cheese, quark, low fat
Description: Soft, fresh cheese similar in texture to cottage cheese.

Name: Dressing, thousand island, reduced fat, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared beige or light orange coloured low oil cream, emulsified sauce used to dress salads and seafood. Formulated to be reduced in fat. Major ingredients include tomato, sugar, vinegar, vegetable oil and gherkin.

Name: Lamb Biryana (lamb & rice), Indian restaurant-style
Description: A mixed dish, typically containing basmati rice, lamb, onions, yogurt, milk, almonds, coriander leaves, cinnamon, cumin, red capsicum, five star spice, dates, curry leaves, boiled egg, glace cherries, pineapple and sultanas, as served in Indian restaurants.

Name: Celeriac, peeled, raw
Description: A thick tuberous root with brown skin and white flesh, with a celery like flavour. Uncooked.

Name: Beverage, chocolate flavour, from base (Milo), with regular fat milk
Description: Beverage prepared by mixing a fortified chocolate flavoured beverage base (Milo brand) with regular fat milk.

Name: Semolina, raw
Description: Coarsely ground starchy product from the inner endosperm of durum wheat. It is granular in appearance and ranges from clear to yellow in colour. Uncooked.

Name: Bar, muffin, fruit flavoured
Description: Fruit flavoured muffin-based snack bar. Major ingredients include sugar syrup, wheat flour, dried fruit and flavours.

Name: Mutton, leg roast, semi-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw mutton from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. Majority of external fat removed.

Name: Ghee, clarified butter
Description: Indian-style clarified butter, at least 99.7% milk fat, used mainly in cooking.

Name: Beef, sirloin steak, separable lean, raw
Description: Raw beef from the midsection of the carcase. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Sugar confectionery, boiled
Description: Hard confectionery made from sugars, food acid, flavours and colours.

Name: Oregano, dried
Description: Dried, and sometimes ground, leaves of Oreganum vulgare, used as a culinary herb.

Name: Cream, sour, extra light (>12% fat)
Description: Commercially produced Australian sour cream. Prepared by culturing a combination of cows milk cream, milk and skim milk with lactic acid bacteria resulting in the sour flavour and decreased fat content compared to regular and light sour cream varieties. Contains >12% milk fat.

Name: Mutton, leg roast, fully-trimmed, roasted
Description: Cooked mutton from the hind portion of the carcase. Oven roasted to an internal temperature of 70C with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Grain waves, flavoured
Description: Cereal based snack product made from wholegrain wheat, oat and corn, with added flavours.

Name: Bread, brown (mixture of white & wholemeal flour)
Description: Bread made from equal parts of wholemeal flour and white flour. Contains added folate and iodised salt. Ready to eat.

Name: Cake, carrot, iced, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared cake prepared from carrot, eggs, flour, sugar and vegetable oil and generally containing walnuts. Contains added icing generally made with cream or neufchatel cheese.

Name: Pakora (coated & deep fried vegetables), Indian restaurant-style
Description: Vegetables such as onion, capsicum and egg plant coated in pea flour and deep fried in vegetable oil, as served with sauce and fresh coriander leaves in Indian restaurants/takeaway shops.

Name: Chocolate, compound, cooking
Description: Cocoa-based product formulated for baking or other cooking purposes in which cocoa butter is wholly or partially replaced with vegetable oils. Generally dark in colour but also includes milk cooking chocolate.

Name: Lamb, leg roast, untrimmed, roasted
