Name: Bar, muesli, plain or with dried fruit, yoghurt-coated
Description: Snack style product whose major ingredients include rolled oats, dried fruits, sugars, vegetable oils. The bar is covered or topped with a yoghurt-based coating.

Name: Biscuit, savoury, from white flour, flaky cracker style
Description: Commercially prepared, square, savoury biscuits made from white wheat flour, with a flaky or layered texture. Arnotts SAO brand is an example of this style of biscuit.

Name: Salmon, pink, canned in water, no added salt, drained
Description: Flesh, bones and skin of fish labelled as being pink salmon. Canned in water without addition of salt, drained.

Name: Wine, red
Description: Alcoholic beverage produced by fermentation of grape juice with prolonged grape skin contact to produce wine of a deep red colour. Approximately 12% v/v alcohol.

Name: Sweetcorn, creamed, canned, heated
Description: Coarsely pureed sweetcorn kernels purchased canned with added thickener (maize starch), salt, sugar and water. Gently heated.

Name: Crumpet, from wholemeal flour, toasted
Description: Yeasted batter-based product containing wholemeal wheat flour, approximately 10 cm in diameter and 1cm thick. It is cooked on one side only and has an open honeycomb structure on the top surface. Contains added folate. Toasted until lightly brown.

Name: Chicken, nugget, purchased from independent & chain takeaway outlets, fried, unspecified oil
Description: Processed chicken lightly coated and crumbed. Cooked by frying in an unspecified frying fat. As purchased from independent takeaway outlets and takeaway chains.

Name: Beef, stir-fry strips or diced, separable fat, dry fried
Description: Cooked internal and external separable fat from 2 different cuts likely to be from various regions of the carcase. Dry fried as purchased, still attached to the lean muscle meat, with no added fat for 3-5 minutes, then dissected.

Name: Topping, fruit-flavoured
Description: Berry-flavoured syrup. Common flavours include strawberry and raspberry syrup. Typical ingredients include sugar, fruit thickener, vegetable gum and other food additives. Used to pour over ice cream and other desserts and to flavour milk.

Name: Chicken, separable fat, composite, raw
Description: Fat able to be separated from the flesh and skin prior to cooking.

Name: Veal, loin chop, fully-trimmed, grilled
Description: Cooked veal from the midsection of the carcase. Grilled for 10 minutes with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Salt, sea
Description: A type of table salt that is predominantly sodium chloride but may contain a number of other minerals.

Name: Cherry, black, canned in syrup, syrup only
Description: Syrup made from water and sugar, used in imported canned black cherries.

Name: Butter, salted
Description: A product derived exclusively from milk and products obtained from milk, principally in the form of an emulsion of the type water-in-oil, containing no less than 80% milkfat. Contains added salt.

Name: Lamb, drumstick, separable lean, raw
Description: Raw lamb from the fore and hind portions of the carcase. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Melon, honey dew, yellow skin, peeled, raw
Description: Yellow skinned melon with white or green flesh.

Name: Potato, fries, deep fried, monounsaturated oil, take-away outlet, salted
Description: Chips made from peeled potatoes. Long and rectangular in shape, approximately 0.5cm wide, deep fried in monounsaturated oil. Salt added after cooking. Served hot.

Name: Bean, red, fresh, boiled, drained
Description: Fresh seeds, generally red in colour, removed from their pod and cooked by boiling in unsalted water, then draining.

Name: Veal, cutlet, separable lean, raw
Description: Raw veal from the midsection of the carcase. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Egg, chicken, whole, poached
Description: Edible portion, including yolk and white (albumen), of the egg of chickens, simmered in acidified water for 3-5 minutes and drained.

Name: Beef, silverside roast, fully-trimmed, roasted without oil or fat
Description: Cooked beef from the hind portion of the carcase. Oven roasted to an internal temperature of 70C with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Ravioli, beef, Italian restaurant- style
Description: Commercially produced minced beef filling enclosed in small pasta envelopes, in tomato-based sauce, with cheese as purchased from Italian restaurants.

Name: Pork, forequarter chop, as purchased, raw
Description: Raw pork from the forequarter of the carcase, as purchased without removal of internal and external fat.

Name: Bread, pizza base, commercial
Description: Pre-prepared pizza bases made from white flour, purchased in supermarkets. Does not contain any toppings.

Name: Prawn, satay, Chinese restaurant-style
Description: Prawns and onion, in satay (peanut-based) sauce as served in Chinese restaurants.

Name: Veal, stir-fry strips, untrimmed, raw
Description: Raw veal, purchased as strips and likely to be from various regions of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal and external fat attached.

Name: Chicken hot salad, Thai restaurant-style
Description: Cooked chicken mince mixed with fresh vegetables, and ground roasted rice in a spicy sauce, as served in Thai restaurants.

Name: Cabbage, savoy, boiled, drained
Description: Round in shape, with tightly packed green wrinkled layers of leaves.  Chopped and cooked by boiling in unsalted water, then drained.

Name: Beef, topside steak, semi-trimmed, roasted
Description: Cooked beef from the hind portion of the carcase. Oven roasted to an internal temperature of 70C with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. Majority of external fat removed after cooking.

Name: Pork, round steak, fully-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw lean muscle meat from the hind portion of the carcase, as purchased with no separable fat.

Name: Beef, rump steak, untrimmed, raw
Description: Raw beef from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal and external fat attached.

Name: Beef, hot chilli, Indonesian restaurant-style
Description: Beef, chilli, nuts (macadamia or candle), garlic, ginger, turmeric, bay leaf in coconut milk, as served in Indonesian restaurants.

Name: Spaghetti in tomato & cheese sauce, canned
Description: Commercially prepared canned pasta product containing spaghetti in tomato and cheese sauce. Includes some low salt varieties.

Name: Morwong, flesh, steamed
Description: Fillets of morwong flesh. Cooked by steaming.

Name: Braised steak & onions, canned, heated
Description: Canned product commonly containing beef steak, onion, cereal, tomato, salt, spice and water.

Name: Mushroom, straw, Asian, canned in brine, drained
Description: Small, tan egg shaped mushrooms, canned in brine, then drained.

Name: Dressing, French, regular fat, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared thin french-inspired sauce used to dress salads. Major ingredients include water, vegetable oil, sugar, vinegar, garlic and spices.

Name: Cheese, feta (fetta), cows milk, reduced fat
Description: Soft cheese made by curdling cows milk with rennet and formulated to have a lower fat content than regular feta cheese. Feta is then sliced, salted and stored in either whey or brine.

Name: Mutton, casserole, untrimmed, casseroled
Description: Raw mutton from the fore portion (shoulder) of the carcase. Browned, simmered in minimal water for 2 hours then drained. Lean muscle meat with internal and external fat attached.

Name: Lamb, mini roast, separable lean, roasted
Description: Cooked lamb from the hind portion of the carcase. Oven roasted to an internal temperature of 70C with no added fat. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Cone, wafer style, for ice cream
Description: Wafer shaped into a cone or similar shape, used for serving ice cream. Typical ingredients are wheat flour, vegetable oil, salt, sodium bicarbonate. May contain other flours, wheatgerm and colours.

Name: Fish roe (caviar), black
Description: Fish eggs, black in colour, packed in spiced brine, then drained. Includes products described as lumpfish caviar or roe or German caviar and products imported into Australia. Other ingredients may include salt, peanut oil, spices and colours.

Name: Bream, flesh, raw
Description: Uncooked flesh portion only of bream.

Name: Veal, loin chop, untrimmed, grilled
Description: Cooked veal from the midsection of the carcase. Grilled for 10 minutes with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with internal and external fat attached.

Name: Scone, plain, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared, dough-like product made from flour, water, sugar, egg and raising agent and then baked. Contains added folate. Commonly served with jam and cream.

Name: Beef, rump steak, untrimmed, grilled
Description: Cooked beef from the hind portion of the carcase. Grilled for 6-10 minutes until 'medium' with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with internal and external fat attached.

Name: Onion ring, battered, fried, beef tallow
Description: Raw onion rings, coated in a wheat flour based battered and then cooked by deep-frying in beef tallow.

Name: Lamb, mini roast, semi-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw lamb from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. Majority of external fat removed.

Name: Beef, rump medallion, separable lean, raw
Description: Raw beef from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Bacon burger patty, purchased frozen, fried
Description: Burger patty commonly containing beef, bacon, vegetable protein, wheat flour, breadcrumbs, onion, bacon flavour, thickener, salt, pepper, mineral salt and water added. Patty fried with either polyunsaturated cooking oil or peanut oil for 3 minutes on each side and drained of excess fat.

Name: Blueberry, canned in syrup, drained
Description: Small, deep blue berry with whitish waxy bloom canned in sugar syrup, then drained.

Name: Potato crisps or chips, reformed, salted
Description: Snack product that consists of reformed sliced potato, deep fried in vegetable oil, salted & packaged. Includes flavoured and unflavoured varieties.

Name: Juice concentrate, orange
Description: Beverage extracted from oranges with subsequent concentration of the juice to approximately one quarter of its original volume. Contains added vitamin C.

Name: Turkey, hindquarter, lean, skin & fat, baked
Description: Flesh, skin and separable fat from the hindquarter (thigh and drumstick) portion of a chicken. Cooked by baking.

Name: Beef panang, Thai restaurant-style
Description: A Thai style curry typically containing beef, coconut milk, curry paste, sugar and fish sauce as served in Thai restaurants.

Name: Sauce, cheese, made with butter & milk, homemade
Description: Home prepared savoury sauce made from butter, white wheat flour, milk and cheddar cheese.

Name: Muffin, cake-style, bran, flavoured
Description: Commercially prepared cake style muffin, with added bran. May be flavoured, but does not contain topping or icing.

Name: Wheat bran, unprocessed
Description: Outer layers of the wheat grain which are removed during the early stages of milling, and do not undergo further processing other than packaging. Maybe coarsely or finely milled.

Name: Lamb, loin chop, fully-trimmed, grilled
Description: Cooked lamb from the midsection of the carcase. Grilled for 6-10 minutes until 'medium' with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Beef, stir-fry strips, untrimmed, raw
Description: Raw beef, purchased as strips and likely to be from various regions of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal and external fat attached.

Name: Chicken, breast, lean, casseroled
Description: Flesh from breast portion of a chicken. Skin removed. Cooked by casseroling with added water, then drained.

Name: Pork, strips, as purchased, raw
Description: Raw lean pork strips, as purchased, likely to be from leg or shoulder steak.

Name: Milk, cow, fluid, regular fat (3.5%), added omega 3 polyunsaturates
Description: Australian produced cows milk product to which sources of omega-3 fatty acids are added. Supplied with fat content of approximately 3.4%.

Name: Pork, medallion or loin steak, separable lean, dry fried
Description: Cooked pork from the midsection of the carcase. Dry fried, as purchased, to an internal temperature of ~70C with a small amount of pork fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Water, tap
Description: Water as supplied through the municipal water system. Values are approximations of those reported across Australia, and may vary according to location or time of year.

Name: Wine, red, sparkling
Description: Alcoholic beverage produced by fermentation of grape juice from red wine grapes, retaining significant quantities of dissolved carbon dioxide. Approximately 13% v/v alcohol.

Name: Calamari, crumbed, fried, from restaurants & takeaway outlets
Description: Squid, sliced into ring shapes, floured or coated in breadcrumbs and deep fried, as purchased from take away food outlets.

Name: Pudding, sticky date, homemade
Description: Home prepared cake-style dessert prepared with chopped dates and served covered in caramel sauce.

Name: Beef, round steak, semi-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw beef from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. All possible external fat removed.

Name: Rice, purchased as parboiled (gold rice), boiled, with added salt
Description: An unhulled grain that has been soaked, pressure-steamed and dried before milling. Process gelatinizes the starch in the grain and infuses some of the nutrients of the bran and germ into the kernels heart. Pale beige in colour. Cooked by boiling in salted water.

Name: Nut, hazelnut, raw
Description: Small, light brown, round nuts with point at the top, hazelnuts have a thin brown skin, inside a smooth, hard shell with a rough round area at the base.

Name: Butter, no added salt
Description: A product derived exclusively from milk and products obtained from milk, principally in the form of an emulsion of the type water-in-oil, containing no less than 80% milkfat. No added salt.

Name: Chocolate, dark, fondant or cream filled
Description: Chocolate confectionery with dark chocolate coating surrounding a thin layer of flavoured fondant filling, typically mint flavoured.

Name: Cod, smoked, raw
Description: Uncooked fillets of cod preserved by cold or liquid smoking so that the fish has an orange colour.

Name: Biscuit, savoury, wholemeal wheat flour, crispbread, puffed
Description: A thin, flat rectangle of puffed, toasted dry bread made from wholemeal wheat flour, some with added bran, malt or rye (e.g.. Cruskit or Crackerbread style).

Name: Squash, button, boiled, drained
Description: Small, rounded vegetable fruit, generally with a yellow skin. Boiled in water without salt or oil, simmered and allowed to cool.

Name: Pork, forequarter chop, as purchased, barbecued
Description: Cooked pork from the forequarter of the carcase, as purchased without removal of internal and external fat. barbecued for 30 minutes without additional oil or fat.

Name: Beef, loin (fillet, sirloin, scotch fillet, t-bone), separable fat, grilled
Description: Cooked internal and external separable fat from 4 different cuts (fillet, sirloin, scotch fillet, T-bone) from the midsection of the carcase. Grilled as purchased, still attached to the lean muscle meat, with no added fat for 6-10 minutes until 'medium', then dissected.

Name: Flathead, flesh, raw
Description: Uncooked fillets of flathead flesh, from the family Platycephalus including species identified as Sand (P. bassenis), Tiger (P. richardsoni) and Rock (P. laevigatus).

Name: Beef, casserole cuts, fully-trimmed, cooked
Description: Cooked beef from the three most common cuts used for making casseroles  including blade steak, chuck steak, round steak. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. Majority of internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Cheese, blue vein
Description: Australian and imported cheese. Prepared by the addition of culture, rennet and mould spores to cows milk.

Name: Lamb, mini roast, fully-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw lamb from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. Majority of internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Juice, apple, sparkling, no added vitamin C
Description: Commercial carbonated beverage prepared by crushing apples and filtering or clarifying the resultant juice.

Name: Soy beverage, regular fat (~3%), unflavoured, unfortified
Description: Beverage prepared from soy beans, purchased ready to drink. Does not contain added vitamins, minerals or artificial flavouring substances.

Name: Breakfast cereal, mixed grain flakes (wheat, oats), added dried fruit, added vitamins B1, B2, B3 & folate & Fe
Description: Breakfast cereal made from flakes of wheat, oats and triticale with dried fruit (sultanas and apricot), sugar and added Fe, B1, B2, B3 and folate.

Name: Pork rind snack
Description: Packaged snack food produced from dried and salted pork rind.

Name: Cheese, haloumy
Description: Salty semi-soft cheese that maintains its texture when cooked.

Name: Cassava, yellow flesh, peeled, raw
Description: Long, coarse brown tuber, with a fibrous yellow flesh. Uncooked.

Name: Bar, fruit, nut & seed
Description: Sweet snack bar containing added fruit, nuts and or seeds such as apricot, coconut, and sesame seed.

Name: Biscuit, sweet, chocolate flavoured
Description: Commercially prepared crunchy chocolate flavoured biscuit, commonly containing wheat flour, cocoa, sugar, fats, and eggs.

Name: Cassata-style ice cream dessert
Description: Australian made, commercially prepared Italian-style ice cream dessert usually containing fruit, nuts and chocolate. May contain alcohol.

Name: Beef, silverside minute steak, separable lean, roasted
Description: Cooked beef from the hind portion of the carcase. Oven roasted to an internal temperature of 70C with no added fat. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Cake, fruit, uniced, homemade
Description: Home prepared fruit cake made from common household ingredients including dried vine fruit (boiled), self raising and plain flours, sugar, butter, eggs and citrus peel, baked.

Name: Beef, heart, simmered
Description: Heart trimmed of fat and vessels, chopped, simmered in water and drained.

Name: Sauce, chocolate, homemade
Description: A thick brown chocolate-flavoured syrup used to top desserts or flavour milk.

Name: Bread, from wholemeal flour, homemade, added salt, toasted
Description: Bread made from wholemeal wheat flour and other household ingredients including, butter, water, sugar, yeast and salt. Cooking by toasting after baking.

Name: Ham & chicken roll, processed luncheon meat
Description: Processed, thinly sliced meat commonly containing pork, beef, chicken, cereal, salt, sugar, spices, soy protein, antioxidant, sodium nitrate/sodium nitrite and water.

Name: Yoghurt, natural, regular fat (~4%)
Description: Australian produced unflavoured (natural) yoghurt. Prepared by pasteurising and homogenising milk of various fat levels before culturing, resulting in a thickened, tangy yoghurt. Contains added milk powder. Does not contain fruit or flavouring.

Name: Milk, canned, evaporated, skim (<0.5% fat)
Description: Prepared by evaporating ~60% of the water content of skim cows milk prior to sterilisation. Supplied with a fat content <0.5%. Canned.

Name: Bread, from white flour, added calcium, toasted
Description: Commercially prepared bread made from white, wheaten bread-making flour and other permitted ingredients. Fortified with calcium and thiamin. Cooked by toasting after purchase.

Name: Juice, orange, no added vitamin c
Description: Commercial beverage prepared from the endocarp of navel oranges. Does not contain added vitamin C or sucrose. Includes juices sold chilled.

Name: Strawberry, raw
Description: Fresh, sweet red berry with small seeds on the exterior.

Name: Beverage base, chocolate flavour, with milk solids, unfortified, intense sweetened
Description: Dry mix used to prepare a hot chocolate flavoured beverage with the addition of water. Mix is sweetened with intense sweeteners instead of sugar. Typical ingredients include maltodextrins, milk solids, vegetable oil and cocoa. Does not contain added vitamins or minerals.

Name: Sausage, vegetarian style, added Fe, Zn and vitamin B12, raw
Description: Sausages made from chopped, minced, or blended vegetables and/or legumes and other ingredients such as spices, sugar and salt. Contains added iron, zinc and vitamin B12.

Name: Snowpea, boiled, drained
Description: A long flat green pod, containing small round green peas. Chopped and cooked by boiling in unsalted water, then drained.

Name: Coffee, instant, dry powder or granules
Description: Dried extract of coffee beans, used to produce a beverage by the addition of boiling water.

Name: Parsnip, peeled, baked without oil
Description: A white root vegetable shaped like a carrot. Peeled, chopped and baked without added oil.

Name: Apple, granny-smith, unpeeled, baked
Description: Round shaped fruit with a green shiny skin and firm, crisp, juicy white flesh. Cooked by baking.

Name: Potato, red skin, peeled, boiled
Description: Round in shape, with a pink to red smooth skin and a creamy yellow flesh. Peeled and boiled in unsalted water, then drained.

Name: Cake, fruit, rich, uniced, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared dark-coloured cake containing large amounts of dried vine fruit, citrus peel and glace cherries.

Name: Potato, sebago, peeled, baked, animal fat
Description: Round in shape, with a smooth whitish skin. Peeled and cooked by baking with animal fat.

Name: Beer, reduced alcohol or light beer
Description: Alcoholic beverage characterised by the presence of hops or preparations of hops, prepared by the yeast fermentation of an aqueous extract of malted or unmalted cereals (usually barley), so as to restrict alcohol formation or to remove alcohol after fermentation. Products are described on label as Light or Lite. Approximately 2.1% v/v alcohol.

Name: Soup, French onion, dry mix
Description: Dry onion soup mix containing dried onion and other ingredients such as mushrooms, herbs, wheat flour, vegetable oil, beverage whitener, milk proteins, salt and vegetable gum. Intended for the preparation of a soup by simmering with added water.

Name: Shark (flake), battered, deep fried, take away
Description: Flesh from various types of shark (typically Gummy, School and Black Tipped shark), coated in battered and deep fried as purchased ready to eat from take away food outlets. Frying medium may be vegetable oil or tallow based fat.

Name: Lamb, frenched cutlet/rack, separable lean, raw
Description: Raw lamb from the midsection of the carcase. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Bar, muesli, with chocolate chips
Description: Snack style product whose major ingredients include rolled oats, sugars, vegetable oil, with embedded chocolate chips. May contain added milk powder.

Name: Bar, cherry & coconut centre, dark chocolate-coated
Description: A cherry and coconut flavoured snack bar coated in a layer of dark chocolate.

Name: Bread, garlic, made with butter, commercial
Description: Sliced white bread to which a mixture of butter, garlic, salt and parsley is added, before the bread is heated to melt the butter mixture. Bread contains added folate and iodised salt.

Name: Mulloway, flesh, crumbed, fried, peanut oil
Description: Fillets of mulloway flesh, coated in wheat flour, egg and breadcrumbs, pan fried in peanut oil, drained. Coating is 15% of uncooked product weight.

Name: Pork, silverside steak, separable lean, dry fried
Description: Cooked lean muscle meat from the hind portion of the carcase. Dry fried, as purchased, to an internal temperature of ~70C with a small amount of pork fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Chillies (chilies), dried, ground
Description: Dried and ground fruit of Capsicum spp, characterised by a hot sensation when consumed as a spice. Includes cayenne pepper, dried ground red pepper.

Name: Venison, diced, lean, raw
Description: Raw diced venison from the forequarter portion of the carcase, with all visible fat removed.

Name: Chicken, drumstick, lean, skin & fat, baked
Description: Flesh, skin and separable fat from drumstick portion of a chicken. Cooked by baking.

Name: Breakfast cereal, whole wheat, flakes, added dried fruit & nuts, added vitamins B1, B2, B3 & folate, Ca, Fe & fibre
Description: Breakfast cereal made from whole wheat flakes with added wheat bran, dried fruit, nuts, salt, calcium, iron, vitamins B1, B2, B3 and folate.

Name: Pasta, beef filled, with tomato based sauce, heated
Description: Commercially prepared pasta dish made from a minced beef filling enclosed in small pasta envelopes, in tomato-based sauce. Includes pasta purchased frozen and heated by boiling at home and pasta dishes purchased from restaurants.

Name: Pear, canned in light syrup, drained
Description: Fruit with a long pear shape with tapering neck, a brown or green skin and yellowish white flesh canned pear in light syrup, then drained.

Name: Biscuit, sweet, with dried fruit, iced
Description: Commercially prepared, sweet biscuit with added dried vine fruit, topped with icing. Prepared from wheat flour with added sugar and fat. May contain added salt, milk powder and other ingredients.

Name: Pepino, peeled, raw
Description: Small melon-shaped fruit, with creamy-green skin, purple stripes and pale yellow flesh with soft edible seeds.

Name: Bar, muesli, with added nuts
Description: Snack style product whose major ingredients include rolled oats, sugars, vegetable oils and nuts (typically cashews, almonds, pecans or macadamias).

Name: Quail, flesh & skin, raw
Description: Raw flesh and skin portion from a quail.

Name: Chicken, coconut cream curry, Vietnamese restaurant-style
Description: Chicken in a coconut cream sauce with vegetables such as capsicum, carrot, peas or onion, as served in Vietnamese restaurants.

Name: Sauce, chilli (chili), Asian, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared sauce based on chillies, salt, sugar and vinegar, commonly used as a condiment in Asian-style cuisines.

Name: Spring roll, meat &/or vegetable, deep fried
Description: Commercially produced unspecified savoury filling rolled in thin pastry, deep fried. Includes spring rolls purchased frozen and served in take away food outlets.

Name: Soup, vegetable, cream style, prepared from simmer dry mix with water
Description: Vegetable soup prepared from a simmer dry mix by mixing with water and simmering for several minutes.

Name: Yoghurt, regular fat, purchased frozen, fruit flavoured
Description: Australian produced frozen fruit yoghurt. Major ingredients include sugar, non-fat milk solids, fruit, glucose, emulsifiers, gums and culture. Prepared by freezing rapidly with agitation to aerate and give a light texture.

Name: Beef, chuck steak, untrimmed, casseroled
Description: Cooked beef from the fore portion of the carcase. Browned, simmered in minimal water for 2 hours then drained. Lean muscle meat with all internal and external fat attached.

Name: Soup, minestrone, homemade
Description: Home prepared soup made from haricot beans, bacon rashers, garlic, onions, carrot, celery, capsicum, tomato puree, cabbage, green peas, macaroni, herbs and spices and water, simmered.

Name: Lamb, easy carve leg roast, untrimmed, raw
Description: Raw lamb from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal and external fat attached.

Name: Cake, banana, uniced, homemade
Description: Home prepared cake made from common household ingredients including flour, banana, sugar, egg, oil and milk.

Name: Soup, cream of chicken, condensed, canned, prepared with milk & water
Description: Condensed cream of chicken canned soup. Prepared according to label instructions with water and milk, then simmered.

Name: Oil, olive
Description: Edible oil pressed from the flesh of the fruit of the olive tree (Olea europaea). Most values are derived from oils produced in Spain or Italy and imported to Australia. Includes various grades of olive oil, such as 'pure' and 'extra virgin'.

Name: Gelatine, powder, unflavoured
Description: Unflavoured light yellow granular proteinaceous powder. Used to sweeten and thicken soups, sauces and desserts.

Name: Chicken, drumstick, lean, raw
Description: Uncooked flesh from drumstick portion of a chicken. Skin removed.

Name: Soft drink, cola flavour, intense sweetened
Description: Carbonated, non-alcoholic beverage containing water, intense sweeteners, cola flavour and colours.

Name: Zucchini, golden, boiled, drained
Description: Variety of squash which has a yellow smooth skin and a cream flesh.  Chopped and boiled in water, drained.

Name: Beef, topside steak, fully-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw beef from the midsection of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. Majority of internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Cumin (cummin) seeds, ground
Description: Dried and ground fruit or seeds of Cuminum cymimum, used as a spice.

Name: Chicken, breast, lean, baked
Description: Flesh from breast portion of the chicken. Skin removed. Cooked by baking.

Name: Flour, cornflour, from maize & wheat starch
Description: Fine white powder extracted from the starchy endosperm of maize (corn) or wheat. Sold in Australia under the name of cornflour.

Name: Dressing, Italian, fat free, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared thin italian-inspired sauce used to dress salads. Formulated to be reduced in fat. Major ingredients include vinegar, sugar and spices.

Name: Chicken pieces, in tandoori sauce, Indian restaurant-style
Description: Chicken commonly marinated with yogurt, lemon juice, chilli powder, ghee, cardamom, tomato paste, cumin seeds, vinegar, turmeric powder and paprika, as served in Indian restaurants.

Name: Black pudding, raw
Description: Sausage with major ingredients of meat, blood, cereal.

Name: Beef, topside roast, separable lean, raw
Description: Raw beef from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Chicken, liver, raw
Description: Liver of chicken trimmed of external fat and large vessels, raw.

Name: Baked beans, canned in tomato sauce, salt reduced
Description: Navy/haricot beans in tomato sauce, canned. Contains added salt, sugar, food acids, maize thickener and flavour. Reduced salt content.

Name: Fish finger, crumbed, purchased frozen, grilled
Description: Rectangular-shaped skinless fish pieces, coated in breadcrumbs and deep fried. Purchased frozen then cooked by grilling according to label instructions.

Name: Pork, loin chop, semi-trimmed, dry-fried
Description: Cooked pork from the lumbar part of the loin, cooked by grilling. Majority of fat is removed after cooking but a small amount (5% of edible portion) remains.

Name: Lamb, BBQ/grill/fry cuts, fully-trimmed, cooked
Description: Cooked lamb from the three most common cuts used for barbecuing, grilling and frying including french cutlet, loin chop and forequarter chop. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Spam, canned
Description: Manufactured pork product containing chopped pork shoulder, leg ham, salt, sugar, mineral salts, sodium nitrite and water.

Name: Noodles, pad thai, Thai restaurant-style
Description: Common Thai dish. Typical ingredients include rice noodles, prawns, egg and bean sprouts, as served in Thai restaurants.

Name: Bread, from wholemeal flour
Description: Commercially prepared, sliced or unsliced bread made from flour containing all the milled constituents of the wheat grain. Contains added folate and iodine, in addition to thiamin. Ready to eat.

Name: Sardine, canned in tomato sauce
Description: Sardines preserved by canning in tomato-based sauce, with added salt.

Name: Couscous, raw
Description: Cream coloured pellets made from approximately 2 parts semolina, 1 part wheat flour and salt and water, then steamed and dried. No further cooking.

Name: Pancake, prepared from dry mix
Description: Pancake prepared from a commercial dry mix according to label instructions.

Name: Beef, all cuts, separable fat, cooked

Name: Biscuit, savoury, from white flour, Salada style
Description: Commercially prepared square biscuits made from white wheat flour with added fat and sprinkled with salt. Arnotts Salada brand crackers are an example of this style of biscuit.

Name: Apricot, canned in light syrup
Description: Small, orange-coloured stone fruit canned in light syrup.

Name: Prawn, crumbed, fried, Chinese restaurant-style
Description: Prawn flesh and tail crumbed and deep fried, as served in Chinese restaurants.

Name: Beef, chuck steak, fully-trimmed, casseroled
Description: Cooked beef from the fore portion of the carcase. Browned, simmered in minimal water for 2 hours then drained. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Pork, mince, as purchased, raw
Description: Raw lean pork mince, as purchased, likely to be from leg or shoulder.

Name: Turnip, white, peeled, raw
Description: A white fleshed root vegetable with purple-flushed white skin. Peeled. Uncooked.

Name: Fruit salad, canned in pear juice, drained
Description: A variety of fruits that have been canned in pear juice, then drained.

Name: Muffin, English style, from white flour, toasted
Description: A round yeasted dough made from white wheat flour, baked on both sides (approximately 8.5cm in diameter and 2cm thick). Contains added folate and iodised salt. Cooked by toasting after purchase until lightly brown.

Name: Flathead, steamed or poached
Description: Fillets of flathead flesh from the family Platycephalus including species identified as Sand (P. bassenis), Tiger (P. richardsoni) and Rock (P. laevigatus). Cooked by steaming.

Name: Lime,  peeled, raw
Description: Oval fruit with light greenish-yellow pulp when ripe.

Name: Bread, from rye flour, dark
Description: Commercially prepared bread made from rye flour, or including a large proportion of rye flour. Contains added folate and iodised salt. Ready to eat.

Name: Pea, green, fresh, boiled, drained
Description: A small round green seed, boiled in unsalted water, then drained.

Name: Cheese, edam
Description: Australian and imported cheese. Made by curdling cows milk with rennet, followed by curing. Coated in oil or a red or yellow wax film.

Name: Bread, from white flour, added omega-3 polyunsaturates, toasted
Description: Commercially prepared bread made from white, wheaten bread-making flour and other permitted ingredients, with added omega-3 fatty acids, folate and iodised salt and thiamin. Cooked by toasting after purchase.

Name: Sugar confectionery, jelly varieties
Description: Confectionery products such as jelly babies, fruit rings, pastilles, fruit gums, jubes.

Name: Curry powder
Description: Dried and ground mixture of spices for use in the preparation of Indian-style meals. Typical ingredients include the spices cumin, coriander seed and turmeric.

Name: Hamburger patty, crumbed, purchased frozen, fried
Description: Hamburger patty commonly containing beef, wheat flour, onion, salt, herbs, spices, mineral salts and water. Patty covered with breadcrumbs. Fried in either polyunsaturated cooking oil or peanut oil for 3 minutes each side, then drained of excess fat.

Name: Pudding, plum, canned, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared canned, cake-style pudding with added dried fruit and citrus peel, commonly consumed at Christmas time. Simmered in can for 20 minutes.

Name: Pizza, ham & pineapple, purchased frozen, baked
Description: Commercially produced pizza dough topped with tomato-based sauce, cheese, ham and pineapple, frozen before packaging and reheated prior to consumption.

Name: Tea, regular, brewed from leaf or teabags, without milk
Description: Beverage prepared by brewing black tea leaves (dried, fermented leaves of Chrysanthemum species) in hot water, either as loose tea leaves or encased in porous teabags. 15g tea leaves in 1L of water. Tea is not decaffeinated or flavoured. Does not contain added milk or sugar.

Name: Intense sweetener, containing saccharin, tablet
Description: Sweetening product in tablet formulation containing sodium saccharin as the intense sweetener. May also contain food additives such as sodium bicarbonate, tartaric acid and stabilisers.

Name: Eggplant, baked without oil
Description: A smooth, shiny deep purple-blackish skinned vegetable with a creamy white interior with many small light brown seeds dispersed through the flesh. Cooked by baking without added oil.

Name: Pie, savoury, meat, commercial, family size
Description: Commercially produced meat-based (usually beef and/or mutton) filling enclosed in a single layer or pastry, ready to eat.

Name: Flour, wheat, wholemeal, self-raising
Description: Flour milled from whole wheat grain (bran, germ and flour) to which chemical leavening agents have been added. No added vitamins or minerals.

Name: Cod, smoked, steamed or poached
Description: Fillets of cod preserved by cold or liquid smoking so that the fish has an orange colour. Cooked by poaching or steaming.

Name: Chicken, tikka, Indian restaurant-style
Description: A chicken-based Indian-style dish consisting of chicken pieces, coated with red chilli powder and coriander leaves.

Name: Coconut, milk or cream, dried, powder
Description: Packaged liquid extracted from the flesh of mature coconuts and then dried to a fine powder. Generally contains added starch or maltodextrin and milk proteins.

Name: Cordial base, 40% citrus fruit juice (orange, lemon or lime)
Description: Concentrated sugar-based syrup containing at least 40% citrus fruit juice (typically orange or lemon juice) juice, used to prepare a beverage by dilution with water.

Name: Tamarillo, peeled, raw
Description: Small fruit with a smooth peel that can be purple, red, orange, or yellow. It has a black or orange flesh (the darker the peel, the darker the flesh) surrounding a nest of seeds.ﾠ

Name: Lamb, loin, separable fat, raw
Description: Raw internal and external separable fat from 1 cut (loin chop) from the midsection of the carcase.

Name: Mutton, casserole, fully-trimmed, casseroled
Description: Raw mutton from the fore portion (shoulder) of the carcase. Browned, simmered in minimal water for 2 hours then drained. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. Majority of internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Cheese, cheddar, regular fat
Description: Australian and imported cheddar cheese. Prepared by curdling cows milk with rennet, followed by curing. Includes unsliced mild, tasty and vintage varieties.

Name: Crocodile, tail fillet, raw
Description: Raw meat from the tail of a crocodile.

Name: Bread, from wholemeal flour, grain & seeds, toasted
Description: Commercially prepared bread made from flour containing all the milled constituents of the wheat grain, kibbled grains and sunflower seeds. Contains added folate, iodised salt and thiamin. Cooked by toasting after purchase.

Name: Fruche (fromais frais), regular fat, strawberry
Description: Creamy dessert of whipped yoghurt or fresh cheese blended with strawberries. Major ingredients include concentrated milk, sugar, strawberries and natural flavours.

Name: Chicken, barbecued, with skin
Description: Whole chicken with skin, cooked in a commercial rotisserie oven. Chicken is generally rubbed with oil, spices and salt. Does not include stuffing.

Name: Salmon, Australian, canned in brine, drained
Description: Fish described as Australian salmon, preserved by canning in brine, drained.

Name: Gravy, prepared from dry powder with water
Description: Gravy powder prepared with water only, according to packet directions. Typical ingredients may include wheat flour, salt, colour, spices and vegetable protein. Does not include products labelled as salt reduced or low salt.

Name: Nutmeg, ground
Description: Dried and ground seed of Myristica fragrans (M. officinalis or M. aromatica), used as a spice.

Name: Doughnut, dusted with cinnamon & sugar
Description: Sweet dough made from yeast, water, milk, sugar, butter, flour, and eggs that is extruded into a ring shape and deep fried in oil. Dusted with cinnamon and sugar after cooking. Contains added folate.

Name: Bacon, breakfast rasher, raw
Description: Raw, cured, smoked and cooked pork rasher produced from chopped and reformed meat and containing salt, sugar, mineral salts, antioxidant, nitrite and water.

Name: Breakfast cereal, whole wheat, biscuit, with bran, added vitamins B1, B2, B3 & folate & Fe
Description: Breakfast cereal made from whole wheat, with added bran, sugar, iron, B1, B2, B3 and folate, and formed into a biscuit shape.

Name: Pea, split, dried
Description: Yellow or green field pea with husks removed. Dry and uncooked.

Name: Pork, leg steak (round, rump, topside, silverside), separable lean, dry fried
Description: Cooked lean muscle meat from 4 cuts (round, rump, topside and silverside) from the hind portion of the carcase. Dry fried, as purchased, to an internal temperature of ~70C with a small amount of pork fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Pate, liverwurst, commercial
Description: Mildly spiced pate made from blended liver, typically pork liver.

Name: Lamb, drumstick, fully-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw lamb from the fore and hind portions of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Beans, refried, canned
Description: Paste prepared from pinto beans pureed with other vegetables and spices, canned.

Name: Bread, from white flour, added fibre, toasted
Description: Commercially prepared bread made from white, wheaten bread-making flour and other permitted ingredients. Contains added fibre and/or added high amylose maize starch, folate, iodised salt and thiamin. Cooked by toasting after purchase.

Name: Fruit drink, 25% orange juice, added vitamin c
Description: Commercially prepared beverage made from 25% orange juice, water and sugars. Contains added vitamin C.

Name: Grape, waltham cross, raw
Description: Elongated oval grapes, golden green with sweet juicy pulp and firm skin.

Name: Slice, fruit mince, iced, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared sweet slice containing a short crust pastry and a dried fruit filling. Contains a sugar based icing topping.

Name: Pork, forequarter, separable fat, barbecued
Description: Cooked internal and external fat from 3 cuts (chop, roast and neck) from the forequarter of the carcase. barbecued or roasted, as purchased, without additional oil or fat, then dissected.

Name: Chicken, separable fat, composite, casseroled
Description: Fat from a fresh chicken, cooked in a casserole dish with added water.

Name: Nut, peanut, with skin, raw
Description: Raw kernels with reddish brown skin produced after removing the shell.

Name: Cider, apple, alcoholic, dry style
Description: Alcoholic beverage prepared from fermented apples, with a low level of residual sugars. Approximately 4% alcohol.

Name: Breakfast cereal, wheat bran, flakes, added vitamins B1, B2 B3, & folate, Fe & Zn
Description: Breakfast cereal made from flakes of wheat bran with added vitamins B1, B2, B3 and folate and added iron and zinc.

Name: Pizza, supreme, purchased frozen, baked
Description: Commercially produced pizza dough topped with tomato-based sauce, cheese, sausage, capsicum, onion, ham, mushrooms and sometimes olives and beef, frozen before packaging and reheated prior to consumption.

Name: Turnip, white, peeled, boiled, drained
Description: A white fleshed tuber vegetable, with purple-flushed white skin. Peeled, chopped and boiled in unsalted water, then drained.

Name: Cucumber, lebanese, unpeeled, raw
Description: Long and cylindrical in shape with dark green skin and white flesh with a crisp texture.  Uncooked.

Name: Bar, nougat & caramel centre, milk chocolate-coated
Description: Chocolate-coated bar with nougat and caramel centre.

Name: Chicken, liver, cooked
Description: Liver of chicken, trimmed of external fat and large vessels, fried in butter until cooked.

Name: Bread, from wheat flour, added dried fruit, toasted
Description: Bread-style loaf made from white wheat flour and containing 13 - 25% added dried fruit. Contains added folate and iodised salt. Cooked by toasting after purchase.

Name: Sports drink, all flavours
Description: Non-alcoholic beverage especially formulated to meet the nutritional needs of sports people. Contains a range of added minerals and vitamins. Composition may vary significantly according to brand.

Name: Bean, soya, canned, drained
Description: Small oval shaped, creamy yellow coloured beans with a floury texture from the pod of soybean plant. Beans canned in sweetened brine, then drained.

Name: Cassava, white flesh, peeled, boiled, drained
Description: Long, coarse brown tuber, with a fibrous white flesh. Cooked by boiling in unsalted water, then drained.

Name: Egg, chicken, white (albumen) only, hard-boiled
Description: White (albumen) portion of chicken eggs, separated from the yolk portion after boiled in shell in unsalted water for 7 minutes until both white and yolk were firm.

Name: Bread, from white flour, toasted
Description: Commercially prepared bread made from white, wheaten bread-making flour and other permitted ingredients. Contains added folate and iodine, in addition to thiamin. Cooked by toasting after purchase.

Name: Apricot, dried
Description: Small, orange-coloured stone fruit dried prior to packaging. May be treated to prevent browning.

Name: Lamb, frenched cutlet/rack, fully-trimmed, grilled
Description: Cooked lamb from the midsection of the carcase. Grilled for 6-10 minutes until 'medium' with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Beef, blade steak, separable fat, grilled
Description: Cooked internal and external separable fat from 1 cut from the fore portion of the carcase. Grilled as purchased, still attached to the lean muscle meat, with no added fat for 6-10 minutes until 'medium', then dissected.

Name: Pork, loin chop, separable fat, raw
Description: Raw internal and external separable fat from the lumbar part of loin.

Name: Intense sweetener, containing aspartame, powdered formulation
Description: Sweetening product in powdered formulation containing aspartame as the intense sweetener, also containing lactose and food additives.

Name: Hundreds & thousands
Description: Small coloured and brittle balls of sugar that are usually sprinkled on other foods. Main ingredients include white sugar, cornflour, water, colours and flavours.

Name: Beer, reduced alcohol or light beer, home-brewed
Description: Alcoholic beverage characterised by the presence of hops or preparations of hops, prepared by the yeast fermentation of an aqueous extract of malted or unmalted cereals (usually barley), and with a lower alcohol content than usual. Approximately 2.1% v/v alcohol.

Name: Bean, soya, dried
Description: Small oval shaped, creamy yellow coloured beans with a floury texture from the pod of soybean plant.

Name: Pear, canned in syrup, drained
Description: Fruit with a long pear shape with tapering neck, a brown or green skin and yellowish white flesh canned pear in syrup, then drained.

Name: Broccoli, fresh, boiled, drained
Description: Deep green flower clusters which form the head with pale green stems. Boiled in unsalted water then drained

Name: Cream, pure, 35% fat
Description: Australian produced cows milk cream. Supplied with a fat content of 35%.

Name: Beverage base, sports supplement powder, vanilla flavour, added nutrients
Description: Vanilla flavoured dry beverage base, which is intended to be mixed with water or milk to form a beverage that is specifically formulated to assist sports performance. Typical ingredients include non-fat milk solids, glucose and up to 8 added vitamins and minerals.

Name: Beef, diced, separable lean, raw
Description: Raw beef, purchased diced and likely to be from various regions of the carcase. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Yoghurt, soy based, with mango
Description: Yoghurt-style sweet product based on soy milk rather than dairy milk, with added mango.

Name: Devon or fritz, processed luncheon meat
Description: Processed sandwich meat containing pork, beef, starch, soy protein, cereal, sugar, spices, antioxidants, sodium nitrate/nitrite and water.

Name: Duck, lean, skin & fat, baked
Description: Flesh, skin and fat from all portions of the duck. Cooked by baking.

Name: Egg, quail, whole, raw
Description: Edible portion (including yolk and white) of the egg of the quail. Uncooked

Name: Peach, canned in syrup, drained
Description: Small stone fruit with a reddish/orange furry skin and orange flesh canned in heavy syrup, then drained.

Name: Dairy blend, butter & edible oil spread, 70% fat, reduced salt
Description: A spread that is a blend of approximately two-thirds butter and one-third vegetable oil, generally canola oil. Total fat content is somewhat reduced from regular dairy blend, to around 70%. Reduced salt content. Contains added vitamins A and D.

Name: Blue grenadier (hoki), flesh, baked
Description: Flesh portion only of blue grenadier (commonly known as hoki). Cooked by baking without the addition of fat or oil.  Data refer to fish from New Zealand imported into Australia.

Name: Beef, round steak, separable fat, raw
Description: Raw internal and external separable fat from 1 cut from the hind portion of the carcase.

Name: Beef, tripe, simmered
Description: Typically made from the first three of a cattles four stomachs, the rumen (blanket/flat/smooth tripe), the reticulum (honeycomb and pocket tripe), and the omasum (book/bible/leaf tripe).  Generally sold bleached so that it is white in colour. Tripe chopped, simmered, drained.

Name: Mutton, leg roast, semi-trimmed, roasted
Description: Cooked mutton from the hind portion of the carcase. Oven roasted to an internal temperature of 70C with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. Majority of external fat removed after cooking.

Name: Wine, rose
Description: Alcoholic beverage produced by fermentation of grape juice so that the wine has a pale pink colour. Approximately 11% v/v alcohol.

Name: Artichoke, jerusalem, peeled, raw
Description: Tuber or root, yellow-beige in colour with short knobbly, club shaped branches. Peeled.

Name: Croissant (pastry crescent), commercial, plain
Description: Crescent-shaped pastry prepared from ingredients such as wheat flour, butter (salted or unsalted) or margarine, yeast, sugar, egg, milk powder and food additives, then baked. Sodium content likely to vary widely depending on ingredients.

Name: Ham steak, grilled
Description: Smoked ham steak containing manufactured meat, pork, salt, soya protein, sugar, potato flour, mineral salts, antioxidant, flavours, preservatives, sodium nitrite, water. Cooked by grilling.

Name: Sauce, lemon & butter, homemade
Description: Home made sauce made from butter, sugar, lemon juice, lemon peel, cornflour and water.

Name: Juice, pineapple, sweetened
Description: Commercial beverage prepared from pineapple juice and sugar. Contains added vitamin C.

Name: Lamb, forequarter chop, semi-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw lamb from the fore portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. Majority of external fat removed.

Name: Lobster, flesh only, purchased steamed or boiled
Description: Flesh from lobsters cooked whole in water or steam prior to purchase so that the lobster is red in colour.

Name: Coriander seed, ground
Description: Dried and ground fruit or seed of Coriandrum sativum, used as a spice.

Name: Milk, goat, fluid, regular fat
Description: The mammary secretion of goats obtained from one or more milkings for consumption as liquid milk, excluding colostrum. Pasteurised (regular or ultra-high temperature)  and homogenised.

Name: Pear, brown, unpeeled, raw
Description: Long pear shape with tapering neck, brown skin and yellowish white flesh.

Name: Syrup, maple, pure (100% maple)
Description: Light to medium brown coloured sugar syrup traditionally made by boiling maple tree sap at atmospheric pressure or by freeze-drying it at reduced atmospheric pressure. Imported into Australia.

Name: Soup, chicken & vegetable, with pasta or croutons, cup of soup, instant dry mix
Description: Instant dry chicken, vegetable and noodle soup mix  containing chicken, vegetables (carrot and onion), starch (maize , tapioca), vegetable oil, maltodextrins, flavour enhancers, colour, croutons, pasta (from wheat), mineral salt, antioxidants etc. Requires dilution with boiling water before consumption.

Name: Soup, chicken galanga, Thai restaurant-style
Description: Chicken stock with chicken, coconut milk, galanga slices, coriander leaves, chillies, lemon juice and fish sauce as served in Thai restaurants.

Name: Beef, fillet steak, fully-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw beef from the midsection of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Veal, all cuts, separable fat, cooked
Description: Cooked internal and external separable fat from 4 different cuts from various regions of the carcase. Oven roasted or grilled as purchased, still attached to the lean muscle meat, with no added fat to an internal temperature of 70C or until 'medium', then dissected.

Name: Muffin, cake-style, with fruit, reduced fat, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared cake style muffin with added fruit, formulated to be reduced in fat, as purchased in bakeries and coffee shops.

Name: Bread, from wholemeal flour, grains & seeds
Description: Commercially prepared bread made from flour containing all the milled constituents of the wheat grain, kibbled grains and sunflower seeds. Contains added folate, iodised salt and thiamin. Ready to eat.

Name: Cake, plain butter cake, uniced, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared plain, ready to eat, butter style cake. Typical ingredients include wheat flour, egg, milk powder, sugar, salt, vegetable oil or fat, colours, flavours and baking compounds.

Name: Dairy blend, butter & edible oil spread, 70% fat
Description: A spread that is a blend of approximately two-thirds butter and one-third vegetable oil, generally canola oil. Total fat content is somewhat reduced from regular dairy blend, to around 70%. Contains added salt and vitamins A and D.

Name: Oil, macadamia
Description: Edible oil extracted from the macadamia nut (Macadamia integrifolia).

Name: Sauce, plum, Asian, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared chutney-type, spicy, sweet, hot sauce, based on plums.

Name: Milk, canned, sweetened, condensed, regular
Description: Milk product prepared by adding sugar to whole cows milk prior to evaporation of  approximately 50% of the water content. Both canned and tube varieties included.

Name: Cream, sour, light (~18% fat)
Description: Commercially produced Australian sour cream. Prepared by culturing a combination of cows milk cream and milk with lactic acid bacteria resulting in the sour flavour and decreased fat content compared to regular sour cream. Contains >18% milk fat.

Name: Soy beverage, reduced fat (~ 1.5%), chocolate flavoured, added Ca & vitamins A, B1, B2 & B12
Description: Chocolate flavoured beverage prepared from soy beans, with a reduced fat content (~1.5%) purchased ready to drink. Contains added sugar, calcium, vitamins A, B1, B2 and B12.

Name: Bacon, middle rasher, 75% trimmed, raw
Description: Raw, cured, smoked and cooked pork middle rasher containing salt, sugar, mineral salts, antioxidant, nitrite and water. 75% of fat removed.

Name: Lamb, forequarter chop, untrimmed, raw
Description: Raw lamb from the fore portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal and external fat attached.

Name: Lamb, easy carve leg roast, semi-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw lamb from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. Majority of external fat removed.

Name: Lamb, frenched cutlet/rack, semi-trimmed, grilled
Description: Cooked lamb from the midsection of the carcase. Grilled for 6-10 minutes until 'medium' with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. Majority of external fat removed after cooking.

Name: Apricot, canned in intense sweetened liquid
Description: Small, orange-coloured stone fruit canned in intense sweetened liquid.

Name: Tomato, sundried
Description: Tomatoes that have been left out to dry in the sun.

Name: Ice confection, stick, milk-based, various flavours
Description: Australian produced flavoured ice confection on a stick. Major ingredients include sugar, skim milk/solids, whey and vegetable gums. Flavours include chocolate, strawberry, banana and chocolate-dipped vanilla.

Name: Wax jambu, raw
Description: Pear-shaped fruit with bright to dark pink skin, white flesh and several large brown seeds. Also known as Java Apple- Rose Apple- Makopa- Wax Apple.

Name: Cake, chocolate, prepared from dry mix, uniced
Description: Chocolate flavoured cake prepared from a chocolate cake dry mix, with the addition of eggs, regular fat milk and margarine spread, then baked. Ingredients for preparation vary depending on cake mix brand.

Name: Soy beverage, reduced fat (~1.5% fat), unflavoured, added Ca, Fe & folate
Description: Beverage prepared from soy beans with a reduced fat content (~1.5%), purchased ready to drink. Contains added  calcium, iron and folate, vitamins A, B1, B2 and B12.

Name: Beef, casserole cuts, fully-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw beef from the three most common cuts used for making casseroles including blade steak, chuck steak, round steak. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. Majority of internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Tuna, canned in vegetable oil
Description: Tuna flesh canned in edible oil (including olive oil, canola oil, polyunsaturated oil) with added salt.

Name: Zucchini, green skin, stir-fried without oil
Description: A variety of summer squash, picked when small. Long and cylindrical in shape with green smooth skin and a cream flesh, chopped and stir fried without added oil.

Name: Tuna, canned in brine
Description: Tuna flesh preserved by canning in brine.

Name: Noodle, wheat, instant, flavoured, boiled, drained
Description: Noodle made from wheat flour, vegetable oil, salts and vegetable gums, coiled into blocks and dried before packaging. Cooked by heating in boiling water with contents of favour sachet. Drained of excess water.

Name: Breakfast cereal, whole wheat, biscuit, added vitamins B1, B2, B3 & folate, Fe & Zn
Description: Breakfast cereal prepared from whole wheat, with added sugar, vitamins B1, B2, B3 and folate, iron and zinc. Formed into a biscuit shape. Sanitarium Weet Bix is an example of such a product.

Name: Cucumber, telegraph, unpeeled, raw
Description: Long and cylindrical in shape with dark green skin and white flesh with a crisp texture. Uncooked.

Name: Prawn, salad, Vietnamese restaurant-style
Description: Mixed dish of prawns, carrot, onion, chilli, mint, lemon and peanuts as served in Vietnamese restaurants.

Name: Sauce, bearnaise, homemade
Description: Home prepared creamy sauce made from butter, egg yolk, white wine, vinegar, shallots, parsley, salt and pepper.

Name: Milk, cow, fluid, skim (~0.15% fat)
Description: Australian produced cows skim milk. Prepared by the centrifugal separation of whole pasteurised milk. Supplied with a maximum fat content of 0.15%.

Name: Plum, unpeeled, raw
Description: Small round stone fruit with a deep purple skin and a reddish/purple flesh.

Name: Strawberry, purchased frozen
Description: Sweet red berry with small seeds on the exterior. Frozen prior to sale.

Name: Zucchini, golden, raw
Description: Variety of squash which has a yellow smooth skin and a cream flesh. Uncooked.

Name: Soup, french onion, simmer dry mix
Description: Simmer french onion dry soup mix. Typical ingredients include, dried onions, salt, potato flour, veg. protein, sugar, flavour enhancers, beef fat, cornflour, colour, emulsifier, herbs and spices. Requires dilution with boiling water before consumption.

Name: Juice, carrot
Description: Commercial beverage prepared by pressing raw carrots.

Name: Chocolate, white
Description: Confectionery product that contains milk solids and cocoa butter and is creamy white in colour.

Name: Port (fortified wine)
Description: Sweet, alcoholic beverage prepared from fermented grape juice to which additional alcohol is added. Approximately 14% v/v alcohol.

Name: Lamb, forequarter (easy carve shoulder, forequarter chop), separable fat, raw
Description: Raw internal and external separable fat from 2 different cuts (easy carve shoulder, forequarter chop) from the fore portion of the carcase.

Name: Potato, pale skin, peeled, mashed with milk & butter
Description: Round in shape, with a smooth whitish skin. Peeled and boiled in unsalted water, then drained and mashed with butter and milk.

Name: Pie, sweet, fruit (apple or apricot), commercial, family size
Description: Commercially produced fruit filling enclosed in short crust pastry, ready to eat.

Name: Beef, topside roast, untrimmed, roasted
Description: Cooked beef from the midsection of the carcase. Oven roasted to an internal temperature of 70C with no added fat. Lean muscle meat with internal and external fat attached.

Name: Marinade, Asian style
Description: Asian flavoured marinade used for coating meats prior to cooking.

Name: Prawn, king, garlic, homemade
Description: Flesh of large prawns cooked in olive oil flavoured with garlic, with added lemon juice, salt and pepper, as prepared in the home.

Name: Sardine, canned in water, no added salt, drained
Description: Sardines canned in water without the addition of salt, drained.

Name: Tomato, whole, canned in tomato juice, boiled, drained
Description: Canned, whole peeled tomatoes, heated in salted packing liquid then drained.

Name: Lamb, steak, fully-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw lamb from the hind portion of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. Majority of internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Potato, fries, deep fried, blended oil, take-away outlet, salted
Description: Chips made from peeled potatoes. Long and rectangular in shape, approximately 0.5cm wide, deep fried in blended oil. Salt added after cooking. Served hot.

Name: Potato crisps or chips, plain, unsalted
Description: Snack product that consists of thinly sliced potato, deep fried in vegetable oil and packaged. Does not contain any added flavours or added salt.

Name: Zucchini, green skin, boiled
Description: Variety of marrow or summer squash, picked when small. Long and cylindrical in shape with green smooth skin and a cream flesh. Boiled in water with out salt.

Name: Frankfurt, simmered
Description: Frankfurts sold loose and in vacuum packs, simmered then drained. Commonly contains pork, beef (may also contain mutton and veal), cereal, salt, sugar, spices, soy protein, flavours, preservative, sodium nitrite and water.

Name: Bean, red kidney, dried, boiled, drained
Description: Kidney shaped bean either elongated or plump in shape. Colour ranges from dusky pink to deep red. Beans dried beans, soaked overnight, boiled in unsalted water, then drained.

Name: Lamb, leg roast, separable lean, roasted
Description: Cooked lamb from the hind portion of the carcase. Oven roasted to an internal temperature of 70C with no added fat. Lean muscle meat only, with all possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Fish cake, deep fried, from takeaway outlet
Description: Unspecified fish-based patty, crumbed, deep fried, and salted after cooking, as purchased from take away shops.

Name: Taro, peeled, raw
Description: Tuber vegetable with a light brown rough skin and a cream to pink flesh. Peeled. Uncooked.

Name: Cordial, added fruit juice, recommended dilution
Description: Non-alcoholic beverage prepared by mixing 1 part of a concentrated sugar syrup, typically containing from 25 to 40% fruit juice, with 4 parts of water. Includes fruit cup (typically contains pineapple, orange, lemon and passionfruit juice), orange, lemon and apple raspberry flavours.

Name: Soft drink, lemonade
Description: Carbonated, non-alcoholic beverage prepared from water, sugar and citric acid.

Name: Salmon, Atlantic, grilled
Description: Fillets or cutlets of Atlantic salmon produced by aquaculture. Cooked by grilling without the addition of fat or oil during cooking. Skin removed after cooking.

Name: Soft drink, tonic water, intense sweetened
Description: Carbonated, non-alcoholic beverage prepared from water, intense sweetener and contains quinine.

Name: Cassava, peeled, boiled, drained

Name: Sweetcorn, kernels, purchased frozen, raw

Name: Fruit salad, canned in pineapple juice, drained

Pasta bake sauces commonly contain water, thickener, cheese, onion, garlic, salt, flavours, herbs and spices.

Name: Coconut, fresh, mature, water or juice

Name: Beverage base, chocolate flavour, with milk solids, unfortified

Name: Bread, from rye flour, dark, toasted

Name: Apricot, canned in pear juice, drained

Name: Brussels sprout, fresh, boiled, drained

Name: Salt, cooking

Name: Bread, from white flour, added calcium

Name: Emu, steak, raw
Description: Raw meat from an unspecified portion of an emu.

Name: Parsnip, peeled, raw

Name: Beef, chuck steak, separable fat, raw
